88 /// This switch disables formation of double/multi instructions that could ----
89 /// potentially lead to (new) alignment traps even with CCR.UNALIGN_TRP ----
90 /// disabled. This can be used to create libraries that are robust even when ----
91 /// users provoke undefined behaviour by supplying misaligned pointers. ----
92 /// \see mayCombineMisaligned() ----
93 static cl::opt ----
94 AssumeMisalignedLoadStores("arm-assume-misaligned-load-store", cl::Hidden, ----
95 cl::init(false), cl::desc("Be more conservative in ARM load/store opt")); ----

207 static bool definesCPSR(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
208 for (const auto &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
209 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
210 continue; 0
211 if (MO.isDef() && MO.getReg() == ARM::CPSR && !MO.isDead()) 0
212 // If the instruction has live CPSR def, then it's not safe to fold it ----
213 // into load / store. ----
214 return true; 0
215 } ----
216 ----
217 return false; 0
218 } ----

220 static int getMemoryOpOffset(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
221 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
222 bool isAM3 = Opcode == ARM::LDRD || Opcode == ARM::STRD; 0
223 unsigned NumOperands = MI.getDesc().getNumOperands(); 0
224 unsigned OffField = MI.getOperand(NumOperands - 3).getImm(); 0
225 ----
226 if (Opcode == ARM::t2LDRi12 || Opcode == ARM::t2LDRi8 || 0
227 Opcode == ARM::t2STRi12 || Opcode == ARM::t2STRi8 || 0
228 Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8 || Opcode == ARM::t2STRDi8 || 0
229 Opcode == ARM::LDRi12 || Opcode == ARM::STRi12) 0
230 return OffField; 0
231 ----
232 // Thumb1 immediate offsets are scaled by 4 ----
233 if (Opcode == ARM::tLDRi || Opcode == ARM::tSTRi || 0
234 Opcode == ARM::tLDRspi || Opcode == ARM::tSTRspi) 0
235 return OffField * 4; 0
236 ----
237 int Offset = isAM3 ? ARM_AM::getAM3Offset(OffField) 0
238 : ARM_AM::getAM5Offset(OffField) * 4; 0
239 ARM_AM::AddrOpc Op = isAM3 ? ARM_AM::getAM3Op(OffField) 0
240 : ARM_AM::getAM5Op(OffField); 0
241 ----
242 if (Op == ARM_AM::sub) 0
243 return -Offset; 0
244 ----
245 return Offset; 0
246 } ----

440 static unsigned getLSMultipleTransferSize(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
441 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
442 default: return 0; 0
443 case ARM::LDRi12: 0
444 case ARM::STRi12: ----
445 case ARM::tLDRi: ----
446 case ARM::tSTRi: ----

448 case ARM::tSTRspi: ----

450 case ARM::t2LDRi12: ----
451 case ARM::t2STRi8: ----
452 case ARM::t2STRi12: ----
453 case ARM::VLDRS: ----
454 case ARM::VSTRS: ----
455 return 4; 0
456 case ARM::VLDRD: 0
457 case ARM::VSTRD: ----
458 return 8; 0
459 case ARM::LDMIA: 0
460 case ARM::LDMDA: ----
461 case ARM::LDMDB: ----

477 case ARM::VLDMDIA: 0

483 /// Update future uses of the base register with the offset introduced ----
484 /// due to writeback. This function only works on Thumb1. ----
485 void ARMLoadStoreOpt::UpdateBaseRegUses(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
486 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
487 const DebugLoc &DL, unsigned Base, ----
488 unsigned WordOffset, ----
489 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, ----
490 unsigned PredReg) { ----
491 assert(isThumb1 && "Can only update base register uses for Thumb1!"); 0
492 // Start updating any instructions with immediate offsets. Insert a SUB before ----
493 // the first non-updateable instruction (if any). ----
494 for (; MBBI != MBB.end(); ++MBBI) { 0
495 bool InsertSub = false; 0
496 unsigned Opc = MBBI->getOpcode(); 0
497 ----
498 if (MBBI->readsRegister(Base)) { 0
499 int Offset; ----
500 bool IsLoad = 0
501 Opc == ARM::tLDRi || Opc == ARM::tLDRHi || Opc == ARM::tLDRBi; 0
502 bool IsStore = 0
503 Opc == ARM::tSTRi || Opc == ARM::tSTRHi || Opc == ARM::tSTRBi; 0
504 ----
505 if (IsLoad || IsStore) { 0
506 // Loads and stores with immediate offsets can be updated, but only if ----
507 // the new offset isn't negative. ----
508 // The MachineOperand containing the offset immediate is the last one ----
509 // before predicates. ----
510 MachineOperand &MO = ----
511 MBBI->getOperand(MBBI->getDesc().getNumOperands() - 3); 0
512 // The offsets are scaled by 1, 2 or 4 depending on the Opcode. ----
513 Offset = MO.getImm() - WordOffset * getImmScale(Opc); 0
514 ----
515 // If storing the base register, it needs to be reset first. ----
516 Register InstrSrcReg = getLoadStoreRegOp(*MBBI).getReg(); 0
517 ----
518 if (Offset >= 0 && !(IsStore && InstrSrcReg == Base)) 0
519 MO.setImm(Offset); 0
520 else ----
521 InsertSub = true; 0
522 } else if ((Opc == ARM::tSUBi8 || Opc == ARM::tADDi8) && 0
523 !definesCPSR(*MBBI)) { 0
524 // SUBS/ADDS using this register, with a dead def of the CPSR. ----
525 // Merge it with the update; if the merged offset is too large, ----
526 // insert a new sub instead. ----
527 MachineOperand &MO = ----
528 MBBI->getOperand(MBBI->getDesc().getNumOperands() - 3); 0
529 Offset = (Opc == ARM::tSUBi8) ? 0
530 MO.getImm() + WordOffset * 4 : 0
531 MO.getImm() - WordOffset * 4 ; 0
532 if (Offset >= 0 && TL->isLegalAddImmediate(Offset)) { 0
533 // FIXME: Swap ADDS<->SUBS if Offset < 0, erase instruction if ----
534 // Offset == 0. ----
535 MO.setImm(Offset); 0
536 // The base register has now been reset, so exit early. ----
537 return; 0
538 } else { ----
539 InsertSub = true; 0
540 } ----
541 } else { ----
542 // Can't update the instruction. ----
543 InsertSub = true; 0
544 } ----
545 } else if (definesCPSR(*MBBI) || MBBI->isCall() || MBBI->isBranch()) { 0
546 // Since SUBS sets the condition flags, we can't place the base reset ----
547 // after an instruction that has a live CPSR def. ----
548 // The base register might also contain an argument for a function call. ----
549 InsertSub = true; 0
550 } ----
551 ----
552 if (InsertSub) { 0
553 // An instruction above couldn't be updated, so insert a sub. ----
554 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tSUBi8), Base) 0
555 .add(t1CondCodeOp(true)) 0
556 .addReg(Base) 0
557 .addImm(WordOffset * 4) 0
558 .addImm(Pred) 0
559 .addReg(PredReg); 0
560 return; 0
561 } ----
562 ----
563 if (MBBI->killsRegister(Base) || MBBI->definesRegister(Base)) 0
564 // Register got killed. Stop updating. ----
565 return; 0
566 } ----
567 ----
568 // End of block was reached. ----
569 if (!MBB.succ_empty()) { 0
570 // FIXME: Because of a bug, live registers are sometimes missing from ----
571 // the successor blocks' live-in sets. This means we can't trust that ----
572 // information and *always* have to reset at the end of a block. ----
573 // See PR21029. ----
574 if (MBBI != MBB.end()) --MBBI; 0
575 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(ARM::tSUBi8), Base) 0
576 .add(t1CondCodeOp(true)) 0
577 .addReg(Base) 0
578 .addImm(WordOffset * 4) 0
579 .addImm(Pred) 0
580 .addReg(PredReg); 0
581 } ----
582 } ----
583 ----
584 /// Return the first register of class \p RegClass that is not in \p Regs. ----
585 unsigned ARMLoadStoreOpt::findFreeReg(const TargetRegisterClass &RegClass) { 0
586 if (!RegClassInfoValid) { 0
587 RegClassInfo.runOnMachineFunction(*MF); 0
588 RegClassInfoValid = true; 0
589 } ----
590 ----
591 for (unsigned Reg : RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RegClass)) 0
592 if (LiveRegs.available(MF->getRegInfo(), Reg)) 0
593 return Reg; 0
594 return 0; 0
595 } ----

597 /// Compute live registers just before instruction \p Before (in normal schedule ----
598 /// direction). Computes backwards so multiple queries in the same block must ----
599 /// come in reverse order. ----
600 void ARMLoadStoreOpt::moveLiveRegsBefore(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
601 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator Before) { ----
602 // Initialize if we never queried in this block. ----
603 if (!LiveRegsValid) { 0
604 LiveRegs.init(*TRI); 0
605 LiveRegs.addLiveOuts(MBB); 0
606 LiveRegPos = MBB.end(); 0
607 LiveRegsValid = true; 0
608 } ----
609 // Move backward just before the "Before" position. ----
610 while (LiveRegPos != Before) { 0
611 --LiveRegPos; 0
612 LiveRegs.stepBackward(*LiveRegPos); 0
613 } ----
614 } 0
615 ----
616 static bool ContainsReg(const ArrayRef> &Regs, 0
617 unsigned Reg) { ----
618 for (const std::pair &R : Regs) 0
619 if (R.first == Reg) 0
620 return true; 0
621 return false; 0
622 } ----
623 ----
624 /// Create and insert a LDM or STM with Base as base register and registers in ----
625 /// Regs as the register operands that would be loaded / stored. It returns ----
626 /// true if the transformation is done. ----
627 MachineInstr *ARMLoadStoreOpt::CreateLoadStoreMulti( 0
628 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore, ----
629 int Offset, unsigned Base, bool BaseKill, unsigned Opcode, ----
630 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, unsigned PredReg, const DebugLoc &DL, ----
631 ArrayRef> Regs, ----
632 ArrayRef Instrs) { ----
633 unsigned NumRegs = Regs.size(); 0
634 assert(NumRegs > 1); 0
635 ----
636 // For Thumb1 targets, it might be necessary to clobber the CPSR to merge. ----
637 // Compute liveness information for that register to make the decision. ----
638 bool SafeToClobberCPSR = !isThumb1 || 0
639 (MBB.computeRegisterLiveness(TRI, ARM::CPSR, InsertBefore, 20) == 0
640 MachineBasicBlock::LQR_Dead); 0
641 ----
642 bool Writeback = isThumb1; // Thumb1 LDM/STM have base reg writeback. 0
643 ----
644 // Exception: If the base register is in the input reglist, Thumb1 LDM is ----
645 // non-writeback. ----
646 // It's also not possible to merge an STR of the base register in Thumb1. ----
647 if (isThumb1 && ContainsReg(Regs, Base)) { 0
648 assert(Base != ARM::SP && "Thumb1 does not allow SP in register list"); 0
649 if (Opcode == ARM::tLDRi) 0
650 Writeback = false; 0
651 else if (Opcode == ARM::tSTRi) 0
652 return nullptr; 0
653 } ----
654 ----
655 ARM_AM::AMSubMode Mode = ARM_AM::ia; 0
656 // VFP and Thumb2 do not support IB or DA modes. Thumb1 only supports IA. ----
657 bool isNotVFP = isi32Load(Opcode) || isi32Store(Opcode); 0
658 bool haveIBAndDA = isNotVFP && !isThumb2 && !isThumb1; 0
659 ----
660 if (Offset == 4 && haveIBAndDA) { 0
661 Mode = ARM_AM::ib; 0
662 } else if (Offset == -4 * (int)NumRegs + 4 && haveIBAndDA) { 0
663 Mode = ARM_AM::da; 0
664 } else if (Offset == -4 * (int)NumRegs && isNotVFP && !isThumb1) { 0
665 // VLDM/VSTM do not support DB mode without also updating the base reg. ----
666 Mode = ARM_AM::db; 0
667 } else if (Offset != 0 || Opcode == ARM::tLDRspi || Opcode == ARM::tSTRspi) { 0
668 // Check if this is a supported opcode before inserting instructions to ----
669 // calculate a new base register. ----
670 if (!getLoadStoreMultipleOpcode(Opcode, Mode)) return nullptr; 0
671 ----
672 // If starting offset isn't zero, insert a MI to materialize a new base. ----
673 // But only do so if it is cost effective, i.e. merging more than two ----
674 // loads / stores. ----
675 if (NumRegs <= 2) 0
676 return nullptr; 0
677 ----
678 // On Thumb1, it's not worth materializing a new base register without ----
679 // clobbering the CPSR (i.e. not using ADDS/SUBS). ----
680 if (!SafeToClobberCPSR) 0
681 return nullptr; 0
682 ----
683 unsigned NewBase; ----
684 if (isi32Load(Opcode)) { 0
685 // If it is a load, then just use one of the destination registers ----
686 // as the new base. Will no longer be writeback in Thumb1. ----
687 NewBase = Regs[NumRegs-1].first; 0
688 Writeback = false; 0
689 } else { ----
690 // Find a free register that we can use as scratch register. ----
691 moveLiveRegsBefore(MBB, InsertBefore); 0
692 // The merged instruction does not exist yet but will use several Regs if ----
693 // it is a Store. ----
694 if (!isLoadSingle(Opcode)) 0
695 for (const std::pair &R : Regs) 0
696 LiveRegs.addReg(R.first); 0
697 ----
698 NewBase = findFreeReg(isThumb1 ? ARM::tGPRRegClass : ARM::GPRRegClass); 0
699 if (NewBase == 0) 0
700 return nullptr; 0
701 } ----
702 ----
703 int BaseOpc = isThumb2 ? (BaseKill && Base == ARM::SP ? ARM::t2ADDspImm 0
704 : ARM::t2ADDri) ----
705 : (isThumb1 && Base == ARM::SP) 0
706 ? ARM::tADDrSPi ----
707 : (isThumb1 && Offset < 8) 0
708 ? ARM::tADDi3 ----
709 : isThumb1 ? ARM::tADDi8 : ARM::ADDri; 0
710 ----
711 if (Offset < 0) { 0
712 // FIXME: There are no Thumb1 load/store instructions with negative ----
713 // offsets. So the Base != ARM::SP might be unnecessary. ----
714 Offset = -Offset; 0
715 BaseOpc = isThumb2 ? (BaseKill && Base == ARM::SP ? ARM::t2SUBspImm 0
716 : ARM::t2SUBri) ----
717 : (isThumb1 && Offset < 8 && Base != ARM::SP) 0
718 ? ARM::tSUBi3 ----
719 : isThumb1 ? ARM::tSUBi8 : ARM::SUBri; 0
720 } ----
721 ----
722 if (!TL->isLegalAddImmediate(Offset)) 0
723 // FIXME: Try add with register operand? ----
724 return nullptr; // Probably not worth it then. 0
725 ----
726 // We can only append a kill flag to the add/sub input if the value is not ----
727 // used in the register list of the stm as well. ----
728 bool KillOldBase = BaseKill && 0
729 (!isi32Store(Opcode) || !ContainsReg(Regs, Base)); 0
730 ----
731 if (isThumb1) { 0
732 // Thumb1: depending on immediate size, use either ----
733 // ADDS NewBase, Base, #imm3 ----
734 // or ----
735 // MOV NewBase, Base ----
736 // ADDS NewBase, #imm8. ----
737 if (Base != NewBase && 0
738 (BaseOpc == ARM::tADDi8 || BaseOpc == ARM::tSUBi8)) { 0
739 // Need to insert a MOV to the new base first. ----
740 if (isARMLowRegister(NewBase) && isARMLowRegister(Base) && 0
741 !STI->hasV6Ops()) { 0
742 // thumbv4t doesn't have lo->lo copies, and we can't predicate tMOVSr ----
743 if (Pred != ARMCC::AL) 0
744 return nullptr; 0
745 BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(ARM::tMOVSr), NewBase) 0
746 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(KillOldBase)); 0
747 } else ----
748 BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(ARM::tMOVr), NewBase) 0
749 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(KillOldBase)) 0
750 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)); 0
751 ----
752 // The following ADDS/SUBS becomes an update. ----
753 Base = NewBase; 0
754 KillOldBase = true; 0
755 } ----
756 if (BaseOpc == ARM::tADDrSPi) { 0
757 assert(Offset % 4 == 0 && "tADDrSPi offset is scaled by 4"); 0
758 BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(BaseOpc), NewBase) 0
759 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(KillOldBase)) 0
760 .addImm(Offset / 4) 0
761 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)); 0
762 } else ----
763 BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(BaseOpc), NewBase) 0
764 .add(t1CondCodeOp(true)) 0
765 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(KillOldBase)) 0
766 .addImm(Offset) 0
767 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)); 0
768 } else { ----
769 BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(BaseOpc), NewBase) 0
770 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(KillOldBase)) 0
771 .addImm(Offset) 0
772 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)) 0
773 .add(condCodeOp()); 0
774 } ----
775 Base = NewBase; 0
776 BaseKill = true; // New base is always killed straight away. 0
777 } ----
778 ----
779 bool isDef = isLoadSingle(Opcode); 0
780 ----
781 // Get LS multiple opcode. Note that for Thumb1 this might be an opcode with ----
782 // base register writeback. ----
783 Opcode = getLoadStoreMultipleOpcode(Opcode, Mode); 0
784 if (!Opcode) 0
785 return nullptr; 0
786 ----
787 // Check if a Thumb1 LDM/STM merge is safe. This is the case if: ----
788 // - There is no writeback (LDM of base register), ----
789 // - the base register is killed by the merged instruction, ----
790 // - or it's safe to overwrite the condition flags, i.e. to insert a SUBS ----
791 // to reset the base register. ----
792 // Otherwise, don't merge. ----
793 // It's safe to return here since the code to materialize a new base register ----
794 // above is also conditional on SafeToClobberCPSR. ----
795 if (isThumb1 && !SafeToClobberCPSR && Writeback && !BaseKill) 0
796 return nullptr; 0
797 ----
798 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
799 ----
800 if (Writeback) { 0
801 assert(isThumb1 && "expected Writeback only inThumb1"); 0
802 if (Opcode == ARM::tLDMIA) { 0
803 assert(!(ContainsReg(Regs, Base)) && "Thumb1 can't LDM ! with Base in Regs"); 0
804 // Update tLDMIA with writeback if necessary. ----
805 Opcode = ARM::tLDMIA_UPD; 0
806 } ----
807 ----
808 MIB = BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode)); 0
809 ----
810 // Thumb1: we might need to set base writeback when building the MI. ----
811 MIB.addReg(Base, getDefRegState(true)) 0
812 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(BaseKill)); 0
813 ----
814 // The base isn't dead after a merged instruction with writeback. ----
815 // Insert a sub instruction after the newly formed instruction to reset. ----
816 if (!BaseKill) 0
817 UpdateBaseRegUses(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, Base, NumRegs, Pred, PredReg); 0
818 } else { ----
819 // No writeback, simply build the MachineInstr. ----
820 MIB = BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode)); 0
821 MIB.addReg(Base, getKillRegState(BaseKill)); 0
822 } ----
823 ----
824 MIB.addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
825 ----
826 for (const std::pair &R : Regs) 0
827 MIB.addReg(R.first, getDefRegState(isDef) | getKillRegState(R.second)); 0
828 ----
829 MIB.cloneMergedMemRefs(Instrs); 0
830 ----
831 return MIB.getInstr(); 0
832 } ----
833 ----
834 MachineInstr *ARMLoadStoreOpt::CreateLoadStoreDouble( 0
835 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore, ----
836 int Offset, unsigned Base, bool BaseKill, unsigned Opcode, ----
837 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, unsigned PredReg, const DebugLoc &DL, ----
838 ArrayRef> Regs, ----
839 ArrayRef Instrs) const { ----
840 bool IsLoad = isi32Load(Opcode); 0
841 assert((IsLoad || isi32Store(Opcode)) && "Must have integer load or store"); 0
842 unsigned LoadStoreOpcode = IsLoad ? ARM::t2LDRDi8 : ARM::t2STRDi8; 0
843 ----
844 assert(Regs.size() == 2); 0
845 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DL, 0
846 TII->get(LoadStoreOpcode)); 0
847 if (IsLoad) { 0
848 MIB.addReg(Regs[0].first, RegState::Define) 0
849 .addReg(Regs[1].first, RegState::Define); 0
850 } else { ----
851 MIB.addReg(Regs[0].first, getKillRegState(Regs[0].second)) 0
852 .addReg(Regs[1].first, getKillRegState(Regs[1].second)); 0
853 } ----
854 MIB.addReg(Base).addImm(Offset).addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
855 MIB.cloneMergedMemRefs(Instrs); 0
856 return MIB.getInstr(); 0
857 } ----
858 ----
859 /// Call MergeOps and update MemOps and merges accordingly on success. ----
860 MachineInstr *ARMLoadStoreOpt::MergeOpsUpdate(const MergeCandidate &Cand) { 0
861 const MachineInstr *First = Cand.Instrs.front(); 0
862 unsigned Opcode = First->getOpcode(); 0
863 bool IsLoad = isLoadSingle(Opcode); 0
864 SmallVector, 8> Regs; 0
865 SmallVector ImpDefs; 0
866 DenseSet KilledRegs; 0
867 DenseSet UsedRegs; 0
868 // Determine list of registers and list of implicit super-register defs. ----
869 for (const MachineInstr *MI : Cand.Instrs) { 0
870 const MachineOperand &MO = getLoadStoreRegOp(*MI); 0
871 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
872 bool IsKill = MO.isKill(); 0
873 if (IsKill) 0
874 KilledRegs.insert(Reg); 0
875 Regs.push_back(std::make_pair(Reg, IsKill)); 0
876 UsedRegs.insert(Reg); 0
877 ----
878 if (IsLoad) { 0
879 // Collect any implicit defs of super-registers, after merging we can't ----
880 // be sure anymore that we properly preserved these live ranges and must ----
881 // removed these implicit operands. ----
882 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI->implicit_operands()) { 0
883 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isDef() || MO.isDead()) 0
884 continue; 0
885 assert(MO.isImplicit()); 0
886 Register DefReg = MO.getReg(); 0
887 ----
888 if (is_contained(ImpDefs, DefReg)) 0
889 continue; 0
890 // We can ignore cases where the super-reg is read and written. ----
891 if (MI->readsRegister(DefReg)) 0
892 continue; 0
893 ImpDefs.push_back(DefReg); 0
894 } ----
895 } ----
896 } ----
897 ----
898 // Attempt the merge. ----
899 using iterator = MachineBasicBlock::iterator; ----
900 ----
901 MachineInstr *LatestMI = Cand.Instrs[Cand.LatestMIIdx]; 0
902 iterator InsertBefore = std::next(iterator(LatestMI)); 0
903 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *LatestMI->getParent(); 0
904 unsigned Offset = getMemoryOpOffset(*First); 0
905 Register Base = getLoadStoreBaseOp(*First).getReg(); 0
906 bool BaseKill = LatestMI->killsRegister(Base); 0
907 Register PredReg; 0
908 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*First, PredReg); 0
909 DebugLoc DL = First->getDebugLoc(); 0
910 MachineInstr *Merged = nullptr; 0
911 if (Cand.CanMergeToLSDouble) 0
912 Merged = CreateLoadStoreDouble(MBB, InsertBefore, Offset, Base, BaseKill, 0
913 Opcode, Pred, PredReg, DL, Regs, ----
914 Cand.Instrs); ----
915 if (!Merged && Cand.CanMergeToLSMulti) 0
916 Merged = CreateLoadStoreMulti(MBB, InsertBefore, Offset, Base, BaseKill, 0
917 Opcode, Pred, PredReg, DL, Regs, Cand.Instrs); ----
918 if (!Merged) 0
919 return nullptr; 0
920 ----
921 // Determine earliest instruction that will get removed. We then keep an ----
922 // iterator just above it so the following erases don't invalidated it. ----
923 iterator EarliestI(Cand.Instrs[Cand.EarliestMIIdx]); 0
924 bool EarliestAtBegin = false; 0
925 if (EarliestI == MBB.begin()) { 0
926 EarliestAtBegin = true; 0
927 } else { ----
928 EarliestI = std::prev(EarliestI); 0
929 } ----
930 ----
931 // Remove instructions which have been merged. ----
932 for (MachineInstr *MI : Cand.Instrs) 0
933 MBB.erase(MI); 0
934 ----
935 // Determine range between the earliest removed instruction and the new one. ----
936 if (EarliestAtBegin) 0
937 EarliestI = MBB.begin(); 0
938 else ----
939 EarliestI = std::next(EarliestI); 0
940 auto FixupRange = make_range(EarliestI, iterator(Merged)); 0
941 ----
942 if (isLoadSingle(Opcode)) { 0
943 // If the previous loads defined a super-reg, then we have to mark earlier ----
944 // operands undef; Replicate the super-reg def on the merged instruction. ----
945 for (MachineInstr &MI : FixupRange) { 0
946 for (unsigned &ImpDefReg : ImpDefs) { 0
947 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.implicit_operands()) { 0
948 if (!MO.isReg() || MO.getReg() != ImpDefReg) 0
949 continue; 0
950 if (MO.readsReg()) 0
951 MO.setIsUndef(); 0
952 else if (MO.isDef()) 0
953 ImpDefReg = 0; 0
954 } ----
955 } ----
956 } ----
957 ----
958 MachineInstrBuilder MIB(*Merged->getParent()->getParent(), Merged); 0
959 for (unsigned ImpDef : ImpDefs) 0
960 MIB.addReg(ImpDef, RegState::ImplicitDefine); 0
961 } else { ----
962 // Remove kill flags: We are possibly storing the values later now. ----
963 assert(isi32Store(Opcode) || Opcode == ARM::VSTRS || Opcode == ARM::VSTRD); 0
964 for (MachineInstr &MI : FixupRange) { 0
965 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.uses()) { 0
966 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isKill()) 0
967 continue; 0
968 if (UsedRegs.count(MO.getReg())) 0
969 MO.setIsKill(false); 0
970 } ----
971 } ----
972 assert(ImpDefs.empty()); 0
973 } ----
974 ----
975 return Merged; 0
976 } 0
977 ----
978 static bool isValidLSDoubleOffset(int Offset) { 0
979 unsigned Value = abs(Offset); 0
980 // t2LDRDi8/t2STRDi8 supports an 8 bit immediate which is internally ----
981 // multiplied by 4. ----
982 return (Value % 4) == 0 && Value < 1024; 0
983 } ----
984 ----
985 /// Return true for loads/stores that can be combined to a double/multi ----
986 /// operation without increasing the requirements for alignment. ----
987 static bool mayCombineMisaligned(const TargetSubtargetInfo &STI, 0
988 const MachineInstr &MI) { ----
989 // vldr/vstr trap on misaligned pointers anyway, forming vldm makes no ----
990 // difference. ----
991 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
992 if (!isi32Load(Opcode) && !isi32Store(Opcode)) 0
993 return true; 0
994 ----
995 // Stack pointer alignment is out of the programmers control so we can trust ----
996 // SP-relative loads/stores. ----
997 if (getLoadStoreBaseOp(MI).getReg() == ARM::SP && 0
998 STI.getFrameLowering()->getTransientStackAlign() >= Align(4)) 0
999 return true; 0
1000 return false; 0
1001 } ----
1002 ----
1003 /// Find candidates for load/store multiple merge in list of MemOpQueueEntries. ----
1004 void ARMLoadStoreOpt::FormCandidates(const MemOpQueue &MemOps) { 0
1005 const MachineInstr *FirstMI = MemOps[0].MI; 0
1006 unsigned Opcode = FirstMI->getOpcode(); 0
1007 bool isNotVFP = isi32Load(Opcode) || isi32Store(Opcode); 0
1008 unsigned Size = getLSMultipleTransferSize(FirstMI); 0
1009 ----
1010 unsigned SIndex = 0; 0
1011 unsigned EIndex = MemOps.size(); 0
1012 do { ----
1013 // Look at the first instruction. ----
1014 const MachineInstr *MI = MemOps[SIndex].MI; 0
1015 int Offset = MemOps[SIndex].Offset; 0
1016 const MachineOperand &PMO = getLoadStoreRegOp(*MI); 0
1017 Register PReg = PMO.getReg(); 0
1018 unsigned PRegNum = PMO.isUndef() ? std::numeric_limits::max() 0
1019 : TRI->getEncodingValue(PReg); 0
1020 unsigned Latest = SIndex; 0
1021 unsigned Earliest = SIndex; 0
1022 unsigned Count = 1; 0
1023 bool CanMergeToLSDouble = ----
1024 STI->isThumb2() && isNotVFP && isValidLSDoubleOffset(Offset); 0
1025 // ARM errata 602117: LDRD with base in list may result in incorrect base ----
1026 // register when interrupted or faulted. ----
1027 if (STI->isCortexM3() && isi32Load(Opcode) && 0
1028 PReg == getLoadStoreBaseOp(*MI).getReg()) 0
1029 CanMergeToLSDouble = false; 0
1030 ----
1031 bool CanMergeToLSMulti = true; 0
1032 // On swift vldm/vstm starting with an odd register number as that needs ----
1033 // more uops than single vldrs. ----
1034 if (STI->hasSlowOddRegister() && !isNotVFP && (PRegNum % 2) == 1) 0
1035 CanMergeToLSMulti = false; 0
1036 ----
1037 // LDRD/STRD do not allow SP/PC. LDM/STM do not support it or have it ----
1038 // deprecated; LDM to PC is fine but cannot happen here. ----
1039 if (PReg == ARM::SP || PReg == ARM::PC) 0
1040 CanMergeToLSMulti = CanMergeToLSDouble = false; 0
1041 ----
1042 // Should we be conservative? ----
1043 if (AssumeMisalignedLoadStores && !mayCombineMisaligned(*STI, *MI)) 0
1044 CanMergeToLSMulti = CanMergeToLSDouble = false; 0
1045 ----
1046 // vldm / vstm limit are 32 for S variants, 16 for D variants. ----
1047 unsigned Limit; ----
1048 switch (Opcode) { 0
1049 default: 0
1050 Limit = UINT_MAX; 0
1051 break; 0
1052 case ARM::VLDRD: 0
1053 case ARM::VSTRD: ----
1054 Limit = 16; 0
1055 break; 0
1056 } ----
1057 ----
1058 // Merge following instructions where possible. ----
1059 for (unsigned I = SIndex+1; I < EIndex; ++I, ++Count) { 0
1060 int NewOffset = MemOps[I].Offset; 0
1061 if (NewOffset != Offset + (int)Size) 0
1062 break; 0
1063 const MachineOperand &MO = getLoadStoreRegOp(*MemOps[I].MI); 0
1064 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1065 if (Reg == ARM::SP || Reg == ARM::PC) 0
1066 break; 0
1067 if (Count == Limit) 0
1068 break; 0
1069 ----
1070 // See if the current load/store may be part of a multi load/store. ----
1071 unsigned RegNum = MO.isUndef() ? std::numeric_limits::max() 0
1072 : TRI->getEncodingValue(Reg); 0
1073 bool PartOfLSMulti = CanMergeToLSMulti; 0
1074 if (PartOfLSMulti) { 0
1075 // Register numbers must be in ascending order. ----
1076 if (RegNum <= PRegNum) 0
1077 PartOfLSMulti = false; 0
1078 // For VFP / NEON load/store multiples, the registers must be ----
1079 // consecutive and within the limit on the number of registers per ----
1080 // instruction. ----
1081 else if (!isNotVFP && RegNum != PRegNum+1) 0
1082 PartOfLSMulti = false; 0
1083 } ----
1084 // See if the current load/store may be part of a double load/store. ----
1085 bool PartOfLSDouble = CanMergeToLSDouble && Count <= 1; 0
1086 ----
1087 if (!PartOfLSMulti && !PartOfLSDouble) 0
1088 break; 0
1089 CanMergeToLSMulti &= PartOfLSMulti; 0
1090 CanMergeToLSDouble &= PartOfLSDouble; 0
1091 // Track MemOp with latest and earliest position (Positions are ----
1092 // counted in reverse). ----
1093 unsigned Position = MemOps[I].Position; 0
1094 if (Position < MemOps[Latest].Position) 0
1095 Latest = I; 0
1096 else if (Position > MemOps[Earliest].Position) 0
1097 Earliest = I; 0
1098 // Prepare for next MemOp. ----
1099 Offset += Size; 0
1100 PRegNum = RegNum; 0
1101 } ----
1102 ----
1103 // Form a candidate from the Ops collected so far. ----
1104 MergeCandidate *Candidate = new(Allocator.Allocate()) MergeCandidate; 0
1105 for (unsigned C = SIndex, CE = SIndex + Count; C < CE; ++C) 0
1106 Candidate->Instrs.push_back(MemOps[C].MI); 0
1107 Candidate->LatestMIIdx = Latest - SIndex; 0
1108 Candidate->EarliestMIIdx = Earliest - SIndex; 0
1109 Candidate->InsertPos = MemOps[Latest].Position; 0
1110 if (Count == 1) 0
1111 CanMergeToLSMulti = CanMergeToLSDouble = false; 0
1112 Candidate->CanMergeToLSMulti = CanMergeToLSMulti; 0
1113 Candidate->CanMergeToLSDouble = CanMergeToLSDouble; 0
1114 Candidates.push_back(Candidate); 0
1115 // Continue after the chain. ----
1116 SIndex += Count; 0
1117 } while (SIndex < EIndex); 0
1118 } 0
1119 ----
1120 static unsigned getUpdatingLSMultipleOpcode(unsigned Opc, 0
1121 ARM_AM::AMSubMode Mode) { ----
1122 switch (Opc) { 0
1123 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled opcode!"); 0
1124 case ARM::LDMIA: 0
1125 case ARM::LDMDA: ----
1126 case ARM::LDMDB: ----
1127 case ARM::LDMIB: ----
1128 switch (Mode) { 0
1129 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1130 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::LDMIA_UPD; 0
1131 case ARM_AM::ib: return ARM::LDMIB_UPD; 0
1132 case ARM_AM::da: return ARM::LDMDA_UPD; 0
1133 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::LDMDB_UPD; 0
1134 } ----
1135 case ARM::STMIA: 0
1136 case ARM::STMDA: ----
1137 case ARM::STMDB: ----
1138 case ARM::STMIB: ----
1139 switch (Mode) { 0
1140 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1141 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::STMIA_UPD; 0
1142 case ARM_AM::ib: return ARM::STMIB_UPD; 0
1143 case ARM_AM::da: return ARM::STMDA_UPD; 0
1144 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::STMDB_UPD; 0
1145 } ----
1146 case ARM::t2LDMIA: 0
1147 case ARM::t2LDMDB: ----
1148 switch (Mode) { 0
1149 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1150 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD; 0
1151 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::t2LDMDB_UPD; 0
1152 } ----
1153 case ARM::t2STMIA: 0
1154 case ARM::t2STMDB: ----
1155 switch (Mode) { 0
1156 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1157 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::t2STMIA_UPD; 0
1158 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::t2STMDB_UPD; 0
1159 } ----
1160 case ARM::VLDMSIA: 0
1161 switch (Mode) { 0
1162 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1163 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::VLDMSIA_UPD; 0
1164 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::VLDMSDB_UPD; 0
1165 } ----
1166 case ARM::VLDMDIA: 0
1167 switch (Mode) { 0
1168 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1169 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::VLDMDIA_UPD; 0
1170 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::VLDMDDB_UPD; 0
1171 } ----
1172 case ARM::VSTMSIA: 0
1173 switch (Mode) { 0
1174 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1175 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::VSTMSIA_UPD; 0
1176 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::VSTMSDB_UPD; 0
1177 } ----
1178 case ARM::VSTMDIA: 0
1179 switch (Mode) { 0
1180 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled submode!"); 0
1181 case ARM_AM::ia: return ARM::VSTMDIA_UPD; 0
1182 case ARM_AM::db: return ARM::VSTMDDB_UPD; 0
1183 } ----
1184 } ----
1185 } ----
1186 ----
1187 /// Check if the given instruction increments or decrements a register and ----
1188 /// return the amount it is incremented/decremented. Returns 0 if the CPSR flags ----
1189 /// generated by the instruction are possibly read as well. ----
1190 static int isIncrementOrDecrement(const MachineInstr &MI, Register Reg, 0
1191 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, Register PredReg) { ----
1192 bool CheckCPSRDef; ----
1193 int Scale; ----
1194 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1195 case ARM::tADDi8: Scale = 4; CheckCPSRDef = true; break; 0
1196 case ARM::tSUBi8: Scale = -4; CheckCPSRDef = true; break; 0
1197 case ARM::t2SUBri: 0
1198 case ARM::t2SUBspImm: ----
1199 case ARM::SUBri: Scale = -1; CheckCPSRDef = true; break; 0
1200 case ARM::t2ADDri: 0
1201 case ARM::t2ADDspImm: ----
1202 case ARM::ADDri: Scale = 1; CheckCPSRDef = true; break; 0
1203 case ARM::tADDspi: Scale = 4; CheckCPSRDef = false; break; 0
1204 case ARM::tSUBspi: Scale = -4; CheckCPSRDef = false; break; 0
1205 default: return 0; 0
1206 } ----
1207 ----
1208 Register MIPredReg; 0
1209 if (MI.getOperand(0).getReg() != Reg || 0
1210 MI.getOperand(1).getReg() != Reg || 0
1211 getInstrPredicate(MI, MIPredReg) != Pred || 0
1212 MIPredReg != PredReg) 0
1213 return 0; 0
1214 ----
1215 if (CheckCPSRDef && definesCPSR(MI)) 0
1216 return 0; 0
1217 return MI.getOperand(2).getImm() * Scale; 0
1218 } ----
1219 ----
1220 /// Searches for an increment or decrement of \p Reg before \p MBBI. ----
1221 static MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1222 findIncDecBefore(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, Register Reg, 0
1223 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, Register PredReg, int &Offset) { ----
1224 Offset = 0; 0
1225 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MBBI->getParent(); 0
1226 MachineBasicBlock::iterator BeginMBBI = MBB.begin(); 0
1227 MachineBasicBlock::iterator EndMBBI = MBB.end(); 0
1228 if (MBBI == BeginMBBI) 0
1229 return EndMBBI; 0
1230 ----
1231 // Skip debug values. ----
1232 MachineBasicBlock::iterator PrevMBBI = std::prev(MBBI); 0
1233 while (PrevMBBI->isDebugInstr() && PrevMBBI != BeginMBBI) 0
1234 --PrevMBBI; 0
1235 ----
1236 Offset = isIncrementOrDecrement(*PrevMBBI, Reg, Pred, PredReg); 0
1237 return Offset == 0 ? EndMBBI : PrevMBBI; 0
1238 } ----
1239 ----
1240 /// Searches for a increment or decrement of \p Reg after \p MBBI. ----
1241 static MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1242 findIncDecAfter(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, Register Reg, 0
1243 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, Register PredReg, int &Offset, ----
1244 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1245 Offset = 0; 0
1246 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MBBI->getParent(); 0
1247 MachineBasicBlock::iterator EndMBBI = MBB.end(); 0
1248 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextMBBI = std::next(MBBI); 0
1249 while (NextMBBI != EndMBBI) { 0
1250 // Skip debug values. ----
1251 while (NextMBBI != EndMBBI && NextMBBI->isDebugInstr()) 0
1252 ++NextMBBI; 0
1253 if (NextMBBI == EndMBBI) 0
1254 return EndMBBI; 0
1255 ----
1256 unsigned Off = isIncrementOrDecrement(*NextMBBI, Reg, Pred, PredReg); 0
1257 if (Off) { 0
1258 Offset = Off; 0
1259 return NextMBBI; 0
1260 } ----
1261 ----
1262 // SP can only be combined if it is the next instruction after the original ----
1263 // MBBI, otherwise we may be incrementing the stack pointer (invalidating ----
1264 // anything below the new pointer) when its frame elements are still in ----
1265 // use. Other registers can attempt to look further, until a different use ----
1266 // or def of the register is found. ----
1267 if (Reg == ARM::SP || NextMBBI->readsRegister(Reg, TRI) || 0
1268 NextMBBI->definesRegister(Reg, TRI)) 0
1269 return EndMBBI; 0
1270 ----
1271 ++NextMBBI; 0
1272 } ----
1273 return EndMBBI; 0
1274 } ----
1275 ----
1276 /// Fold proceeding/trailing inc/dec of base register into the ----
1277 /// LDM/STM/VLDM{D|S}/VSTM{D|S} op when possible: ----
1278 /// ----
1279 /// stmia rn, ----
1280 /// rn := rn + 4 * 3; ----
1281 /// => ----
1282 /// stmia rn!, ----
1283 /// ----
1284 /// rn := rn - 4 * 3; ----
1285 /// ldmia rn, ----
1286 /// => ----
1287 /// ldmdb rn!, ----
1288 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::MergeBaseUpdateLSMultiple(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1289 // Thumb1 is already using updating loads/stores. ----
1290 if (isThumb1) return false; 0
1291 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Attempting to merge update of: " << *MI); 0
1292 ----
1293 const MachineOperand &BaseOP = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1294 Register Base = BaseOP.getReg(); 0
1295 bool BaseKill = BaseOP.isKill(); 0
1296 Register PredReg; 0
1297 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*MI, PredReg); 0
1298 unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1299 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1300 ----
1301 // Can't use an updating ld/st if the base register is also a dest ----
1302 // register. e.g. ldmdb r0!, {r0, r1, r2}. The behavior is undefined. ----
1303 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands(), 2)) 0
1304 if (MO.getReg() == Base) 0
1305 return false; 0
1306 ----
1307 int Bytes = getLSMultipleTransferSize(MI); 0
1308 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1309 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI(MI); 0
1310 int Offset; ----
1311 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MergeInstr ----
1312 = findIncDecBefore(MBBI, Base, Pred, PredReg, Offset); 0
1313 ARM_AM::AMSubMode Mode = getLoadStoreMultipleSubMode(Opcode); 0
1314 if (Mode == ARM_AM::ia && Offset == -Bytes) { 0
1315 Mode = ARM_AM::db; 0
1316 } else if (Mode == ARM_AM::ib && Offset == -Bytes) { 0
1317 Mode = ARM_AM::da; 0
1318 } else { ----
1319 MergeInstr = findIncDecAfter(MBBI, Base, Pred, PredReg, Offset, TRI); 0
1320 if (((Mode != ARM_AM::ia && Mode != ARM_AM::ib) || Offset != Bytes) && 0
1321 ((Mode != ARM_AM::da && Mode != ARM_AM::db) || Offset != -Bytes)) { 0
1322 ----
1323 // We couldn't find an inc/dec to merge. But if the base is dead, we ----
1324 // can still change to a writeback form as that will save us 2 bytes ----
1325 // of code size. It can create WAW hazards though, so only do it if ----
1326 // we're minimizing code size. ----
1327 if (!STI->hasMinSize() || !BaseKill) 0
1328 return false; 0
1329 ----
1330 bool HighRegsUsed = false; 0
1331 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands(), 2)) 0
1332 if (MO.getReg() >= ARM::R8) { 0
1333 HighRegsUsed = true; 0
1334 break; 0
1335 } ----
1336 ----
1337 if (!HighRegsUsed) 0
1338 MergeInstr = MBB.end(); 0
1339 else ----
1340 return false; 0
1341 } ----
1342 } ----
1343 if (MergeInstr != MBB.end()) { 0
1344 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Erasing old increment: " << *MergeInstr); 0
1345 MBB.erase(MergeInstr); 0
1346 } ----
1347 ----
1348 unsigned NewOpc = getUpdatingLSMultipleOpcode(Opcode, Mode); 0
1349 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1350 .addReg(Base, getDefRegState(true)) // WB base register 0
1351 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(BaseKill)) 0
1352 .addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
1353 ----
1354 // Transfer the rest of operands. ----
1355 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands(), 3)) 0
1356 MIB.add(MO); 0
1357 ----
1358 // Transfer memoperands. ----
1359 MIB.setMemRefs(MI->memoperands()); 0
1360 ----
1361 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new load/store: " << *MIB); 0
1362 MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
1363 return true; 0
1364 } 0
1365 ----
1366 static unsigned getPreIndexedLoadStoreOpcode(unsigned Opc, 0
1367 ARM_AM::AddrOpc Mode) { ----
1368 switch (Opc) { 0
1369 case ARM::LDRi12: 0
1370 return ARM::LDR_PRE_IMM; 0
1371 case ARM::STRi12: 0
1372 return ARM::STR_PRE_IMM; 0
1373 case ARM::VLDRS: 0
1374 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VLDMSIA_UPD : ARM::VLDMSDB_UPD; 0
1375 case ARM::VLDRD: 0
1376 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VLDMDIA_UPD : ARM::VLDMDDB_UPD; 0
1377 case ARM::VSTRS: 0
1378 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VSTMSIA_UPD : ARM::VSTMSDB_UPD; 0
1379 case ARM::VSTRD: 0
1380 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VSTMDIA_UPD : ARM::VSTMDDB_UPD; 0
1381 case ARM::t2LDRi8: 0
1382 case ARM::t2LDRi12: ----
1383 return ARM::t2LDR_PRE; 0
1384 case ARM::t2STRi8: 0
1385 case ARM::t2STRi12: ----
1386 return ARM::t2STR_PRE; 0
1387 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled opcode!"); 0
1388 } ----
1389 } ----
1390 ----
1391 static unsigned getPostIndexedLoadStoreOpcode(unsigned Opc, 0
1392 ARM_AM::AddrOpc Mode) { ----
1393 switch (Opc) { 0
1394 case ARM::LDRi12: 0
1395 return ARM::LDR_POST_IMM; 0
1396 case ARM::STRi12: 0
1397 return ARM::STR_POST_IMM; 0
1398 case ARM::VLDRS: 0
1399 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VLDMSIA_UPD : ARM::VLDMSDB_UPD; 0
1400 case ARM::VLDRD: 0
1401 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VLDMDIA_UPD : ARM::VLDMDDB_UPD; 0
1402 case ARM::VSTRS: 0
1403 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VSTMSIA_UPD : ARM::VSTMSDB_UPD; 0
1404 case ARM::VSTRD: 0
1405 return Mode == ARM_AM::add ? ARM::VSTMDIA_UPD : ARM::VSTMDDB_UPD; 0
1406 case ARM::t2LDRi8: 0
1407 case ARM::t2LDRi12: ----
1408 return ARM::t2LDR_POST; 0
1409 case ARM::t2LDRBi8: 0
1410 case ARM::t2LDRBi12: ----
1411 return ARM::t2LDRB_POST; 0
1412 case ARM::t2LDRSBi8: 0
1413 case ARM::t2LDRSBi12: ----
1414 return ARM::t2LDRSB_POST; 0
1415 case ARM::t2LDRHi8: 0
1416 case ARM::t2LDRHi12: ----
1417 return ARM::t2LDRH_POST; 0
1418 case ARM::t2LDRSHi8: 0
1419 case ARM::t2LDRSHi12: ----
1420 return ARM::t2LDRSH_POST; 0
1421 case ARM::t2STRi8: 0
1422 case ARM::t2STRi12: ----
1423 return ARM::t2STR_POST; 0
1424 case ARM::t2STRBi8: 0
1425 case ARM::t2STRBi12: ----
1426 return ARM::t2STRB_POST; 0
1427 case ARM::t2STRHi8: 0
1428 case ARM::t2STRHi12: ----
1429 return ARM::t2STRH_POST; 0
1430 ----
1431 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16: 0
1432 return ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16_post; 0
1433 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32: 0
1434 return ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32_post; 0
1435 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16: 0
1436 return ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16_post; 0
1437 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32: 0
1438 return ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32_post; 0
1439 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32: 0
1440 return ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32_post; 0
1441 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32: 0
1442 return ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32_post; 0
1443 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8: 0
1444 return ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8_post; 0
1445 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16: 0
1446 return ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16_post; 0
1447 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32: 0
1448 return ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32_post; 0
1449 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB16: 0
1450 return ARM::MVE_VSTRB16_post; 0
1451 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB32: 0
1452 return ARM::MVE_VSTRB32_post; 0
1453 case ARM::MVE_VSTRH32: 0
1454 return ARM::MVE_VSTRH32_post; 0
1455 case ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8: 0
1456 return ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8_post; 0
1457 case ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16: 0
1458 return ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16_post; 0
1459 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32: 0
1460 return ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32_post; 0
1461 ----
1462 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled opcode!"); 0
1463 } ----
1464 } ----
1465 ----
1466 /// Fold proceeding/trailing inc/dec of base register into the ----
1467 /// LDR/STR/FLD{D|S}/FST{D|S} op when possible: ----
1468 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::MergeBaseUpdateLoadStore(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1469 // Thumb1 doesn't have updating LDR/STR. ----
1470 // FIXME: Use LDM/STM with single register instead. ----
1471 if (isThumb1) return false; 0
1472 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Attempting to merge update of: " << *MI); 0
1473 ----
1474 Register Base = getLoadStoreBaseOp(*MI).getReg(); 0
1475 bool BaseKill = getLoadStoreBaseOp(*MI).isKill(); 0
1476 unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1477 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1478 bool isAM5 = (Opcode == ARM::VLDRD || Opcode == ARM::VLDRS || 0
1479 Opcode == ARM::VSTRD || Opcode == ARM::VSTRS); 0
1480 bool isAM2 = (Opcode == ARM::LDRi12 || Opcode == ARM::STRi12); 0
1481 if (isi32Load(Opcode) || isi32Store(Opcode)) 0
1482 if (MI->getOperand(2).getImm() != 0) 0
1483 return false; 0
1484 if (isAM5 && ARM_AM::getAM5Offset(MI->getOperand(2).getImm()) != 0) 0
1485 return false; 0
1486 ----
1487 // Can't do the merge if the destination register is the same as the would-be ----
1488 // writeback register. ----
1489 if (MI->getOperand(0).getReg() == Base) 0
1490 return false; 0
1491 ----
1492 Register PredReg; 0
1493 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*MI, PredReg); 0
1494 int Bytes = getLSMultipleTransferSize(MI); 0
1495 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1496 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI(MI); 0
1497 int Offset; ----
1498 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MergeInstr ----
1499 = findIncDecBefore(MBBI, Base, Pred, PredReg, Offset); 0
1500 unsigned NewOpc; ----
1501 if (!isAM5 && Offset == Bytes) { 0
1502 NewOpc = getPreIndexedLoadStoreOpcode(Opcode, ARM_AM::add); 0
1503 } else if (Offset == -Bytes) { 0
1504 NewOpc = getPreIndexedLoadStoreOpcode(Opcode, ARM_AM::sub); 0
1505 } else { ----
1506 MergeInstr = findIncDecAfter(MBBI, Base, Pred, PredReg, Offset, TRI); 0
1507 if (MergeInstr == MBB.end()) 0
1508 return false; 0
1509 ----
1510 NewOpc = getPostIndexedLoadStoreOpcode(Opcode, ARM_AM::add); 0
1511 if ((isAM5 && Offset != Bytes) || 0
1512 (!isAM5 && !isLegalAddressImm(NewOpc, Offset, TII))) { 0
1513 NewOpc = getPostIndexedLoadStoreOpcode(Opcode, ARM_AM::sub); 0
1514 if (isAM5 || !isLegalAddressImm(NewOpc, Offset, TII)) 0
1515 return false; 0
1516 } ----
1517 } ----
1518 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Erasing old increment: " << *MergeInstr); 0
1519 MBB.erase(MergeInstr); 0
1520 ----
1521 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Offset < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add; 0
1522 ----
1523 bool isLd = isLoadSingle(Opcode); 0
1524 if (isAM5) { 0
1525 // VLDM[SD]_UPD, VSTM[SD]_UPD ----
1526 // (There are no base-updating versions of VLDR/VSTR instructions, but the ----
1527 // updating load/store-multiple instructions can be used with only one ----
1528 // register.) ----
1529 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1530 auto MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1531 .addReg(Base, getDefRegState(true)) // WB base register 0
1532 .addReg(Base, getKillRegState(isLd ? BaseKill : false)) 0
1533 .addImm(Pred) 0
1534 .addReg(PredReg) 0
1535 .addReg(MO.getReg(), (isLd ? getDefRegState(true) 0
1536 : getKillRegState(MO.isKill()))) 0
1537 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1538 (void)MIB; ----
1539 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new instruction: " << *MIB); 0
1540 } else if (isLd) { 0
1541 if (isAM2) { 0
1542 // LDR_PRE, LDR_POST ----
1543 if (NewOpc == ARM::LDR_PRE_IMM || NewOpc == ARM::LDRB_PRE_IMM) { 0
1544 auto MIB = ----
1545 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc), MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1546 .addReg(Base, RegState::Define) 0
1547 .addReg(Base) 0
1548 .addImm(Offset) 0
1549 .addImm(Pred) 0
1550 .addReg(PredReg) 0
1551 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1552 (void)MIB; ----
1553 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new instruction: " << *MIB); 0
1554 } else { 0
1555 int Imm = ARM_AM::getAM2Opc(AddSub, abs(Offset), ARM_AM::no_shift); 0
1556 auto MIB = ----
1557 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc), MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1558 .addReg(Base, RegState::Define) 0
1559 .addReg(Base) 0
1560 .addReg(0) 0
1561 .addImm(Imm) 0
1562 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)) 0
1563 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1564 (void)MIB; ----
1565 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new instruction: " << *MIB); 0
1566 } ----
1567 } else { ----
1568 // t2LDR_PRE, t2LDR_POST ----
1569 auto MIB = ----
1570 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc), MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1571 .addReg(Base, RegState::Define) 0
1572 .addReg(Base) 0
1573 .addImm(Offset) 0
1574 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)) 0
1575 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1576 (void)MIB; ----
1577 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new instruction: " << *MIB); 0
1578 } ----
1579 } else { ----
1580 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1581 // FIXME: post-indexed stores use am2offset_imm, which still encodes ----
1582 // the vestigal zero-reg offset register. When that's fixed, this clause ----
1583 // can be removed entirely. ----
1584 if (isAM2 && NewOpc == ARM::STR_POST_IMM) { 0
1585 int Imm = ARM_AM::getAM2Opc(AddSub, abs(Offset), ARM_AM::no_shift); 0
1586 // STR_PRE, STR_POST ----
1587 auto MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc), Base) 0
1588 .addReg(MO.getReg(), getKillRegState(MO.isKill())) 0
1589 .addReg(Base) 0
1590 .addReg(0) 0
1591 .addImm(Imm) 0
1592 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)) 0
1593 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1594 (void)MIB; ----
1595 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new instruction: " << *MIB); 0
1596 } else { 0
1597 // t2STR_PRE, t2STR_POST ----
1598 auto MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc), Base) 0
1599 .addReg(MO.getReg(), getKillRegState(MO.isKill())) 0
1600 .addReg(Base) 0
1601 .addImm(Offset) 0
1602 .add(predOps(Pred, PredReg)) 0
1603 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1604 (void)MIB; ----
1605 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new instruction: " << *MIB); 0
1606 } ----
1607 } ----
1608 MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
1609 ----
1610 return true; 0
1611 } 0
1612 ----
1613 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::MergeBaseUpdateLSDouble(MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1614 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1615 assert((Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8 || Opcode == ARM::t2STRDi8) && 0
1616 "Must have t2STRDi8 or t2LDRDi8"); ----
1617 if (MI.getOperand(3).getImm() != 0) 0
1618 return false; 0
1619 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Attempting to merge update of: " << MI); 0
1620 ----
1621 // Behaviour for writeback is undefined if base register is the same as one ----
1622 // of the others. ----
1623 const MachineOperand &BaseOp = MI.getOperand(2); 0
1624 Register Base = BaseOp.getReg(); 0
1625 const MachineOperand &Reg0Op = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1626 const MachineOperand &Reg1Op = MI.getOperand(1); 0
1627 if (Reg0Op.getReg() == Base || Reg1Op.getReg() == Base) 0
1628 return false; 0
1629 ----
1630 Register PredReg; 0
1631 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(MI, PredReg); 0
1632 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI(MI); 0
1633 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
1634 int Offset; ----
1635 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MergeInstr = findIncDecBefore(MBBI, Base, Pred, 0
1636 PredReg, Offset); ----
1637 unsigned NewOpc; ----
1638 if (Offset == 8 || Offset == -8) { 0
1639 NewOpc = Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8 ? ARM::t2LDRD_PRE : ARM::t2STRD_PRE; 0
1640 } else { ----
1641 MergeInstr = findIncDecAfter(MBBI, Base, Pred, PredReg, Offset, TRI); 0
1642 if (MergeInstr == MBB.end()) 0
1643 return false; 0
1644 NewOpc = Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8 ? ARM::t2LDRD_POST : ARM::t2STRD_POST; 0
1645 if (!isLegalAddressImm(NewOpc, Offset, TII)) 0
1646 return false; 0
1647 } ----
1648 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Erasing old increment: " << *MergeInstr); 0
1649 MBB.erase(MergeInstr); 0
1650 ----
1651 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1652 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(NewOpc)); 0
1653 if (NewOpc == ARM::t2LDRD_PRE || NewOpc == ARM::t2LDRD_POST) { 0
1654 MIB.add(Reg0Op).add(Reg1Op).addReg(BaseOp.getReg(), RegState::Define); 0
1655 } else { ----
1656 assert(NewOpc == ARM::t2STRD_PRE || NewOpc == ARM::t2STRD_POST); 0
1657 MIB.addReg(BaseOp.getReg(), RegState::Define).add(Reg0Op).add(Reg1Op); 0
1658 } ----
1659 MIB.addReg(BaseOp.getReg(), RegState::Kill) 0
1660 .addImm(Offset).addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
1661 assert(TII->get(Opcode).getNumOperands() == 6 && 0
1662 TII->get(NewOpc).getNumOperands() == 7 && ----
1663 "Unexpected number of operands in Opcode specification."); ----
1664 ----
1665 // Transfer implicit operands. ----
1666 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.implicit_operands()) 0
1667 MIB.add(MO); 0
1668 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1669 ----
1670 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Added new load/store: " << *MIB); 0
1671 MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
1672 return true; 0
1673 } 0
1674 ----
1675 /// Returns true if instruction is a memory operation that this pass is capable ----
1676 /// of operating on. ----
1677 static bool isMemoryOp(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1678 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1679 switch (Opcode) { 0
1680 case ARM::VLDRS: 0
1681 case ARM::VSTRS: ----
1682 case ARM::VLDRD: ----
1683 case ARM::VSTRD: ----
1684 case ARM::LDRi12: ----
1685 case ARM::STRi12: ----
1686 case ARM::tLDRi: ----
1687 case ARM::tSTRi: ----
1688 case ARM::tLDRspi: ----
1689 case ARM::tSTRspi: ----
1690 case ARM::t2LDRi8: ----
1691 case ARM::t2LDRi12: ----
1692 case ARM::t2STRi8: ----
1693 case ARM::t2STRi12: ----
1694 break; 0
1695 default: 0
1696 return false; 0
1697 } ----
1698 if (!MI.getOperand(1).isReg()) 0
1699 return false; 0
1700 ----
1701 // When no memory operands are present, conservatively assume unaligned, ----
1702 // volatile, unfoldable. ----
1703 if (!MI.hasOneMemOperand()) 0
1704 return false; 0
1705 ----
1706 const MachineMemOperand &MMO = **MI.memoperands_begin(); 0
1707 ----
1708 // Don't touch volatile memory accesses - we may be changing their order. ----
1709 // TODO: We could allow unordered and monotonic atomics here, but we need to ----
1710 // make sure the resulting ldm/stm is correctly marked as atomic. ----
1711 if (MMO.isVolatile() || MMO.isAtomic()) 0
1712 return false; 0
1713 ----
1714 // Unaligned ldr/str is emulated by some kernels, but unaligned ldm/stm is ----
1715 // not. ----
1716 if (MMO.getAlign() < Align(4)) 0
1717 return false; 0
1718 ----
1719 // str could probably be eliminated entirely, but for now we just want ----
1720 // to avoid making a mess of it. ----
1721 // FIXME: Use str as a wildcard to enable better stm folding. ----
1722 if (MI.getOperand(0).isReg() && MI.getOperand(0).isUndef()) 0
1723 return false; 0
1724 ----
1725 // Likewise don't mess with references to undefined addresses. ----
1726 if (MI.getOperand(1).isUndef()) 0
1727 return false; 0
1728 ----
1729 return true; 0
1730 } ----
1731 ----
1732 static void InsertLDR_STR(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1733 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI, int Offset, ----
1734 bool isDef, unsigned NewOpc, unsigned Reg, ----
1735 bool RegDeadKill, bool RegUndef, unsigned BaseReg, ----
1736 bool BaseKill, bool BaseUndef, ARMCC::CondCodes Pred, ----
1737 unsigned PredReg, const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
1738 MachineInstr *MI) { ----
1739 if (isDef) { 0
1740 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1741 TII->get(NewOpc)) ----
1742 .addReg(Reg, getDefRegState(true) | getDeadRegState(RegDeadKill)) 0
1743 .addReg(BaseReg, getKillRegState(BaseKill)|getUndefRegState(BaseUndef)); 0
1744 MIB.addImm(Offset).addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
1745 // FIXME: This is overly conservative; the new instruction accesses 4 ----
1746 // bytes, not 8. ----
1747 MIB.cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1748 } else { ----
1749 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1750 TII->get(NewOpc)) ----
1751 .addReg(Reg, getKillRegState(RegDeadKill) | getUndefRegState(RegUndef)) 0
1752 .addReg(BaseReg, getKillRegState(BaseKill)|getUndefRegState(BaseUndef)); 0
1753 MIB.addImm(Offset).addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
1754 // FIXME: This is overly conservative; the new instruction accesses 4 ----
1755 // bytes, not 8. ----
1756 MIB.cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1757 } ----
1758 } 0
1759 ----
1760 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::FixInvalidRegPairOp(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1761 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { ----
1762 MachineInstr *MI = &*MBBI; 0
1763 unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1764 // FIXME: Code/comments below check Opcode == t2STRDi8, but this check returns ----
1765 // if we see this opcode. ----
1766 if (Opcode != ARM::LDRD && Opcode != ARM::STRD && Opcode != ARM::t2LDRDi8) 0
1767 return false; 0
1768 ----
1769 const MachineOperand &BaseOp = MI->getOperand(2); 0
1770 Register BaseReg = BaseOp.getReg(); 0
1771 Register EvenReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1772 Register OddReg = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1773 unsigned EvenRegNum = TRI->getDwarfRegNum(EvenReg, false); 0
1774 unsigned OddRegNum = TRI->getDwarfRegNum(OddReg, false); 0
1775 ----
1776 // ARM errata 602117: LDRD with base in list may result in incorrect base ----
1777 // register when interrupted or faulted. ----
1778 bool Errata602117 = EvenReg == BaseReg && 0
1779 (Opcode == ARM::LDRD || Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8) && STI->isCortexM3(); 0
1780 // ARM LDRD/STRD needs consecutive registers. ----
1781 bool NonConsecutiveRegs = (Opcode == ARM::LDRD || Opcode == ARM::STRD) && 0
1782 (EvenRegNum % 2 != 0 || EvenRegNum + 1 != OddRegNum); 0
1783 ----
1784 if (!Errata602117 && !NonConsecutiveRegs) 0
1785 return false; 0
1786 ----
1787 bool isT2 = Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8 || Opcode == ARM::t2STRDi8; 0
1788 bool isLd = Opcode == ARM::LDRD || Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8; 0
1789 bool EvenDeadKill = isLd ? 0
1790 MI->getOperand(0).isDead() : MI->getOperand(0).isKill(); 0
1791 bool EvenUndef = MI->getOperand(0).isUndef(); 0
1792 bool OddDeadKill = isLd ? 0
1793 MI->getOperand(1).isDead() : MI->getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1794 bool OddUndef = MI->getOperand(1).isUndef(); 0
1795 bool BaseKill = BaseOp.isKill(); 0
1796 bool BaseUndef = BaseOp.isUndef(); 0
1797 assert((isT2 || MI->getOperand(3).getReg() == ARM::NoRegister) && 0
1798 "register offset not handled below"); ----
1799 int OffImm = getMemoryOpOffset(*MI); 0
1800 Register PredReg; 0
1801 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*MI, PredReg); 0
1802 ----
1803 if (OddRegNum > EvenRegNum && OffImm == 0) { 0
1804 // Ascending register numbers and no offset. It's safe to change it to a ----
1805 // ldm or stm. ----
1806 unsigned NewOpc = (isLd) 0
1807 ? (isT2 ? ARM::t2LDMIA : ARM::LDMIA) 0
1808 : (isT2 ? ARM::t2STMIA : ARM::STMIA); ----
1809 if (isLd) { 0
1810 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1811 .addReg(BaseReg, getKillRegState(BaseKill)) 0
1812 .addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg) 0
1813 .addReg(EvenReg, getDefRegState(isLd) | getDeadRegState(EvenDeadKill)) 0
1814 .addReg(OddReg, getDefRegState(isLd) | getDeadRegState(OddDeadKill)) 0
1815 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1816 ++NumLDRD2LDM; 0
1817 } else { ----
1818 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1819 .addReg(BaseReg, getKillRegState(BaseKill)) 0
1820 .addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg) 0
1821 .addReg(EvenReg, 0
1822 getKillRegState(EvenDeadKill) | getUndefRegState(EvenUndef)) 0
1823 .addReg(OddReg, 0
1824 getKillRegState(OddDeadKill) | getUndefRegState(OddUndef)) 0
1825 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
1826 ++NumSTRD2STM; 0
1827 } ----
1828 } else { 0
1829 // Split into two instructions. ----
1830 unsigned NewOpc = (isLd) 0
1831 ? (isT2 ? (OffImm < 0 ? ARM::t2LDRi8 : ARM::t2LDRi12) : ARM::LDRi12) 0
1832 : (isT2 ? (OffImm < 0 ? ARM::t2STRi8 : ARM::t2STRi12) : ARM::STRi12); ----
1833 // Be extra careful for thumb2. t2LDRi8 can't reference a zero offset, ----
1834 // so adjust and use t2LDRi12 here for that. ----
1835 unsigned NewOpc2 = (isLd) 0
1836 ? (isT2 ? (OffImm+4 < 0 ? ARM::t2LDRi8 : ARM::t2LDRi12) : ARM::LDRi12) 0
1837 : (isT2 ? (OffImm+4 < 0 ? ARM::t2STRi8 : ARM::t2STRi12) : ARM::STRi12); ----
1838 // If this is a load, make sure the first load does not clobber the base ----
1839 // register before the second load reads it. ----
1840 if (isLd && TRI->regsOverlap(EvenReg, BaseReg)) { 0
1841 assert(!TRI->regsOverlap(OddReg, BaseReg)); 0
1842 InsertLDR_STR(MBB, MBBI, OffImm + 4, isLd, NewOpc2, OddReg, OddDeadKill, 0
1843 false, BaseReg, false, BaseUndef, Pred, PredReg, TII, MI); ----
1844 InsertLDR_STR(MBB, MBBI, OffImm, isLd, NewOpc, EvenReg, EvenDeadKill, 0
1845 false, BaseReg, BaseKill, BaseUndef, Pred, PredReg, TII, ----
1846 MI); ----
1847 } else { ----
1848 if (OddReg == EvenReg && EvenDeadKill) { 0
1849 // If the two source operands are the same, the kill marker is ----
1850 // probably on the first one. e.g. ----
1851 // t2STRDi8 killed %r5, %r5, killed %r9, 0, 14, %reg0 ----
1852 EvenDeadKill = false; 0
1853 OddDeadKill = true; 0
1854 } ----
1855 // Never kill the base register in the first instruction. ----
1856 if (EvenReg == BaseReg) 0
1857 EvenDeadKill = false; 0
1858 InsertLDR_STR(MBB, MBBI, OffImm, isLd, NewOpc, EvenReg, EvenDeadKill, 0
1859 EvenUndef, BaseReg, false, BaseUndef, Pred, PredReg, TII, ----
1860 MI); ----
1861 InsertLDR_STR(MBB, MBBI, OffImm + 4, isLd, NewOpc2, OddReg, OddDeadKill, 0
1862 OddUndef, BaseReg, BaseKill, BaseUndef, Pred, PredReg, TII, ----
1863 MI); ----
1864 } ----
1865 if (isLd) 0
1866 ++NumLDRD2LDR; 0
1867 else ----
1868 ++NumSTRD2STR; 0
1869 } ----
1870 ----
1871 MBBI = MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
1872 return true; 0
1873 } ----
1874 ----
1875 /// An optimization pass to turn multiple LDR / STR ops of the same base and ----
1876 /// incrementing offset into LDM / STM ops. ----
1877 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::LoadStoreMultipleOpti(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1878 MemOpQueue MemOps; 0
1879 unsigned CurrBase = 0; 0
1880 unsigned CurrOpc = ~0u; 0
1881 ARMCC::CondCodes CurrPred = ARMCC::AL; 0
1882 unsigned Position = 0; 0
1883 assert(Candidates.size() == 0); 0
1884 assert(MergeBaseCandidates.size() == 0); 0
1885 LiveRegsValid = false; 0
1886 ----
1887 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB.end(), MBBI; I != MBB.begin(); 0
1888 I = MBBI) { 0
1889 // The instruction in front of the iterator is the one we look at. ----
1890 MBBI = std::prev(I); 0
1891 if (FixInvalidRegPairOp(MBB, MBBI)) 0
1892 continue; 0
1893 ++Position; 0
1894 ----
1895 if (isMemoryOp(*MBBI)) { 0
1896 unsigned Opcode = MBBI->getOpcode(); 0
1897 const MachineOperand &MO = MBBI->getOperand(0); 0
1898 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1899 Register Base = getLoadStoreBaseOp(*MBBI).getReg(); 0
1900 Register PredReg; 0
1901 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*MBBI, PredReg); 0
1902 int Offset = getMemoryOpOffset(*MBBI); 0
1903 if (CurrBase == 0) { 0
1904 // Start of a new chain. ----
1905 CurrBase = Base; 0
1906 CurrOpc = Opcode; 0
1907 CurrPred = Pred; 0
1908 MemOps.push_back(MemOpQueueEntry(*MBBI, Offset, Position)); 0
1909 continue; 0
1910 } ----
1911 // Note: No need to match PredReg in the next if. ----
1912 if (CurrOpc == Opcode && CurrBase == Base && CurrPred == Pred) { 0
1913 // Watch out for: ----
1914 // r4 := ldr [r0, #8] ----
1915 // r4 := ldr [r0, #4] ----
1916 // or ----
1917 // r0 := ldr [r0] ----
1918 // If a load overrides the base register or a register loaded by ----
1919 // another load in our chain, we cannot take this instruction. ----
1920 bool Overlap = false; 0
1921 if (isLoadSingle(Opcode)) { 0
1922 Overlap = (Base == Reg); 0
1923 if (!Overlap) { 0
1924 for (const MemOpQueueEntry &E : MemOps) { 0
1925 if (TRI->regsOverlap(Reg, E.MI->getOperand(0).getReg())) { 0
1926 Overlap = true; 0
1927 break; 0
1928 } ----
1929 } ----
1930 } ----
1931 } ----
1932 ----
1933 if (!Overlap) { 0
1934 // Check offset and sort memory operation into the current chain. ----
1935 if (Offset > MemOps.back().Offset) { 0
1936 MemOps.push_back(MemOpQueueEntry(*MBBI, Offset, Position)); 0
1937 continue; 0
1938 } else { ----
1939 MemOpQueue::iterator MI, ME; ----
1940 for (MI = MemOps.begin(), ME = MemOps.end(); MI != ME; ++MI) { 0
1941 if (Offset < MI->Offset) { 0
1942 // Found a place to insert. ----
1943 break; 0
1944 } ----
1945 if (Offset == MI->Offset) { 0
1946 // Collision, abort. ----
1947 MI = ME; 0
1948 break; 0
1949 } ----
1950 } ----
1951 if (MI != MemOps.end()) { 0
1952 MemOps.insert(MI, MemOpQueueEntry(*MBBI, Offset, Position)); 0
1953 continue; 0
1954 } ----
1955 } ----
1956 } ----
1957 } ----
1958 ----
1959 // Don't advance the iterator; The op will start a new chain next. ----
1960 MBBI = I; 0
1961 --Position; 0
1962 // Fallthrough to look into existing chain. ----
1963 } else if (MBBI->isDebugInstr()) { 0
1964 continue; 0
1965 } else if (MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2LDRDi8 || 0
1966 MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2STRDi8) { 0
1967 // ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt has already formed some LDRD/STRD instructions ----
1968 // remember them because we may still be able to merge add/sub into them. ----
1969 MergeBaseCandidates.push_back(&*MBBI); 0
1970 } ----
1971 ----
1972 // If we are here then the chain is broken; Extract candidates for a merge. ----
1973 if (MemOps.size() > 0) { 0
1974 FormCandidates(MemOps); 0
1975 // Reset for the next chain. ----
1976 CurrBase = 0; 0
1977 CurrOpc = ~0u; 0
1978 CurrPred = ARMCC::AL; 0
1979 MemOps.clear(); 0
1980 } ----
1981 } ----
1982 if (MemOps.size() > 0) 0
1983 FormCandidates(MemOps); 0
1984 ----
1985 // Sort candidates so they get processed from end to begin of the basic ----
1986 // block later; This is necessary for liveness calculation. ----
1987 auto LessThan = [](const MergeCandidate* M0, const MergeCandidate *M1) { 0
1988 return M0->InsertPos < M1->InsertPos; 0
1989 }; ----
1990 llvm::sort(Candidates, LessThan); 0
1991 ----
1992 // Go through list of candidates and merge. ----
1993 bool Changed = false; 0
1994 for (const MergeCandidate *Candidate : Candidates) { 0
1995 if (Candidate->CanMergeToLSMulti || Candidate->CanMergeToLSDouble) { 0
1996 MachineInstr *Merged = MergeOpsUpdate(*Candidate); 0
1997 // Merge preceding/trailing base inc/dec into the merged op. ----
1998 if (Merged) { 0
1999 Changed = true; 0
2000 unsigned Opcode = Merged->getOpcode(); 0
2001 if (Opcode == ARM::t2STRDi8 || Opcode == ARM::t2LDRDi8) 0
2002 MergeBaseUpdateLSDouble(*Merged); 0
2003 else ----
2004 MergeBaseUpdateLSMultiple(Merged); 0
2005 } else { ----
2006 for (MachineInstr *MI : Candidate->Instrs) { 0
2007 if (MergeBaseUpdateLoadStore(MI)) 0
2008 Changed = true; 0
2009 } ----
2010 } ----
2011 } else { 0
2012 assert(Candidate->Instrs.size() == 1); 0
2013 if (MergeBaseUpdateLoadStore(Candidate->Instrs.front())) 0
2014 Changed = true; 0
2015 } ----
2016 } ----
2017 Candidates.clear(); 0
2018 // Try to fold add/sub into the LDRD/STRD formed by ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt. ----
2019 for (MachineInstr *MI : MergeBaseCandidates) 0
2020 MergeBaseUpdateLSDouble(*MI); 0
2021 MergeBaseCandidates.clear(); 0
2022 ----
2023 return Changed; 0
2024 } 0
2025 ----
2026 /// If this is a exit BB, try merging the return ops ("bx lr" and "mov pc, lr") ----
2027 /// into the preceding stack restore so it directly restore the value of LR ----
2028 /// into pc. ----
2029 /// ldmfd sp!, {..., lr} ----
2030 /// bx lr ----
2031 /// or ----
2032 /// ldmfd sp!, {..., lr} ----
2033 /// mov pc, lr ----
2034 /// => ----
2035 /// ldmfd sp!, {..., pc} ----
2036 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::MergeReturnIntoLDM(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
2037 // Thumb1 LDM doesn't allow high registers. ----
2038 if (isThumb1) return false; 0
2039 if (MBB.empty()) return false; 0
2040 ----
2041 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
2042 if (MBBI != MBB.begin() && MBBI != MBB.end() && 0
2043 (MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::BX_RET || 0
2044 MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::tBX_RET || 0
2045 MBBI->getOpcode() == ARM::MOVPCLR)) { 0
2046 MachineBasicBlock::iterator PrevI = std::prev(MBBI); 0
2047 // Ignore any debug instructions. ----
2048 while (PrevI->isDebugInstr() && PrevI != MBB.begin()) 0
2049 --PrevI; 0
2050 MachineInstr &PrevMI = *PrevI; 0
2051 unsigned Opcode = PrevMI.getOpcode(); 0
2052 if (Opcode == ARM::LDMIA_UPD || Opcode == ARM::LDMDA_UPD || 0
2053 Opcode == ARM::LDMDB_UPD || Opcode == ARM::LDMIB_UPD || 0
2054 Opcode == ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD || Opcode == ARM::t2LDMDB_UPD) { 0
2055 MachineOperand &MO = PrevMI.getOperand(PrevMI.getNumOperands() - 1); 0
2056 if (MO.getReg() != ARM::LR) 0
2057 return false; 0
2058 unsigned NewOpc = (isThumb2 ? ARM::t2LDMIA_RET : ARM::LDMIA_RET); 0
2059 assert(((isThumb2 && Opcode == ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD) || 0
2060 Opcode == ARM::LDMIA_UPD) && "Unsupported multiple load-return!"); ----
2061 PrevMI.setDesc(TII->get(NewOpc)); 0
2062 MO.setReg(ARM::PC); 0
2063 PrevMI.copyImplicitOps(*MBB.getParent(), *MBBI); 0
2064 MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
2065 // We now restore LR into PC so it is not live-out of the return block ----
2066 // anymore: Clear the CSI Restored bit. ----
2067 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MBB.getParent()->getFrameInfo(); 0
2068 // CSI should be fixed after PrologEpilog Insertion ----
2069 assert(MFI.isCalleeSavedInfoValid() && "CSI should be valid"); 0
2070 for (CalleeSavedInfo &Info : MFI.getCalleeSavedInfo()) { 0
2071 if (Info.getReg() == ARM::LR) { 0
2072 Info.setRestored(false); 0
2073 break; 0
2074 } ----
2075 } ----
2076 return true; 0
2077 } ----
2078 } ----
2079 return false; 0
2080 } ----
2081 ----
2082 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::CombineMovBx(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
2083 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.getFirstTerminator(); 0
2084 if (MBBI == MBB.begin() || MBBI == MBB.end() || 0
2085 MBBI->getOpcode() != ARM::tBX_RET) 0
2086 return false; 0
2087 ----
2088 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Prev = MBBI; 0
2089 --Prev; 0
2090 if (Prev->getOpcode() != ARM::tMOVr || !Prev->definesRegister(ARM::LR)) 0
2091 return false; 0
2092 ----
2093 for (auto Use : Prev->uses()) 0
2094 if (Use.isKill()) { 0
2095 assert(STI->hasV4TOps()); 0
2096 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MBBI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::tBX)) 0
2097 .addReg(Use.getReg(), RegState::Kill) 0
2098 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)) 0
2099 .copyImplicitOps(*MBBI); 0
2100 MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
2101 MBB.erase(Prev); 0
2102 return true; 0
2103 } ----
2104 ----
2105 llvm_unreachable("tMOVr doesn't kill a reg before tBX_RET?"); 0
2106 } ----
2107 ----
2108 bool ARMLoadStoreOpt::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &Fn) { 0
2109 if (skipFunction(Fn.getFunction())) 0
2110 return false; 0
2111 ----
2112 MF = &Fn; 0
2113 STI = &Fn.getSubtarget(); 0
2114 TL = STI->getTargetLowering(); 0
2115 AFI = Fn.getInfo(); 0
2116 TII = STI->getInstrInfo(); 0
2117 TRI = STI->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2118 ----
2119 RegClassInfoValid = false; 0
2120 isThumb2 = AFI->isThumb2Function(); 0
2121 isThumb1 = AFI->isThumbFunction() && !isThumb2; 0
2122 ----
2123 bool Modified = false; 0
2124 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : Fn) { 0
2125 Modified |= LoadStoreMultipleOpti(MBB); 0
2126 if (STI->hasV5TOps() && !AFI->shouldSignReturnAddress()) 0
2127 Modified |= MergeReturnIntoLDM(MBB); 0
2128 if (isThumb1) 0
2129 Modified |= CombineMovBx(MBB); 0
2130 } ----
2131 ----
2132 Allocator.DestroyAll(); 0
2133 return Modified; 0
2134 } ----
