2194 // Limit the number of instructions to be rescheduled. ----
2195 // FIXME: tune this limit, and/or come up with some better heuristics. ----
2196 static cl::opt InstReorderLimit("arm-prera-ldst-opt-reorder-limit", ----
2197 cl::init(8), cl::Hidden); ----
2198 ----
2199 bool ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &Fn) { 0
2200 if (AssumeMisalignedLoadStores || skipFunction(Fn.getFunction())) 0
2201 return false; 0
2202 ----
2203 TD = &Fn.getDataLayout(); 0
2204 STI = &Fn.getSubtarget(); 0
2205 TII = STI->getInstrInfo(); 0
2206 TRI = STI->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2207 MRI = &Fn.getRegInfo(); 0
2208 DT = &getAnalysis(); 0
2209 MF = &Fn; 0
2210 AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
2211 ----
2212 bool Modified = DistributeIncrements(); 0
2213 for (MachineBasicBlock &MFI : Fn) 0
2214 Modified |= RescheduleLoadStoreInstrs(&MFI); 0
2215 ----
2216 return Modified; 0
2217 } ----
2218 ----
2219 static bool IsSafeAndProfitableToMove(bool isLd, unsigned Base, 0
2220 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, ----
2221 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E, ----
2222 SmallPtrSetImpl &MemOps, ----
2223 SmallSet &MemRegs, ----
2224 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
2225 AliasAnalysis *AA) { ----
2226 // Are there stores / loads / calls between them? ----
2227 SmallSet AddedRegPressure; 0
2228 while (++I != E) { 0
2229 if (I->isDebugInstr() || MemOps.count(&*I)) 0
2230 continue; 0
2231 if (I->isCall() || I->isTerminator() || I->hasUnmodeledSideEffects()) 0
2232 return false; 0
2233 if (I->mayStore() || (!isLd && I->mayLoad())) 0
2234 for (MachineInstr *MemOp : MemOps) 0
2235 if (I->mayAlias(AA, *MemOp, /*UseTBAA*/ false)) 0
2236 return false; 0
2237 for (unsigned j = 0, NumOps = I->getNumOperands(); j != NumOps; ++j) { 0
2238 MachineOperand &MO = I->getOperand(j); 0
2239 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
2240 continue; 0
2241 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
2242 if (MO.isDef() && TRI->regsOverlap(Reg, Base)) 0
2243 return false; 0
2244 if (Reg != Base && !MemRegs.count(Reg)) 0
2245 AddedRegPressure.insert(Reg); 0
2246 } ----
2247 } ----
2248 ----
2249 // Estimate register pressure increase due to the transformation. ----
2250 if (MemRegs.size() <= 4) 0
2251 // Ok if we are moving small number of instructions. ----
2252 return true; 0
2253 return AddedRegPressure.size() <= MemRegs.size() * 2; 0
2254 } 0
2255 ----
2256 bool ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt::CanFormLdStDWord( 0
2257 MachineInstr *Op0, MachineInstr *Op1, DebugLoc &dl, unsigned &NewOpc, ----
2258 Register &FirstReg, Register &SecondReg, Register &BaseReg, int &Offset, ----
2259 Register &PredReg, ARMCC::CondCodes &Pred, bool &isT2) { ----
2260 // Make sure we're allowed to generate LDRD/STRD. ----
2261 if (!STI->hasV5TEOps()) 0
2262 return false; 0
2263 ----
2264 // FIXME: VLDRS / VSTRS -> VLDRD / VSTRD ----
2265 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
2266 unsigned Opcode = Op0->getOpcode(); 0
2267 if (Opcode == ARM::LDRi12) { 0
2268 NewOpc = ARM::LDRD; 0
2269 } else if (Opcode == ARM::STRi12) { 0
2270 NewOpc = ARM::STRD; 0
2271 } else if (Opcode == ARM::t2LDRi8 || Opcode == ARM::t2LDRi12) { 0
2272 NewOpc = ARM::t2LDRDi8; 0
2273 Scale = 4; 0
2274 isT2 = true; 0
2275 } else if (Opcode == ARM::t2STRi8 || Opcode == ARM::t2STRi12) { 0
2276 NewOpc = ARM::t2STRDi8; 0
2277 Scale = 4; 0
2278 isT2 = true; 0
2279 } else { ----
2280 return false; 0
2281 } ----
2282 ----
2283 // Make sure the base address satisfies i64 ld / st alignment requirement. ----
2284 // At the moment, we ignore the memoryoperand's value. ----
2285 // If we want to use AliasAnalysis, we should check it accordingly. ----
2286 if (!Op0->hasOneMemOperand() || 0
2287 (*Op0->memoperands_begin())->isVolatile() || 0
2288 (*Op0->memoperands_begin())->isAtomic()) 0
2289 return false; 0
2290 ----
2291 Align Alignment = (*Op0->memoperands_begin())->getAlign(); 0
2292 Align ReqAlign = STI->getDualLoadStoreAlignment(); 0
2293 if (Alignment < ReqAlign) 0
2294 return false; 0
2295 ----
2296 // Then make sure the immediate offset fits. ----
2297 int OffImm = getMemoryOpOffset(*Op0); 0
2298 if (isT2) { 0
2299 int Limit = (1 << 8) * Scale; 0
2300 if (OffImm >= Limit || (OffImm <= -Limit) || (OffImm & (Scale-1))) 0
2301 return false; 0
2302 Offset = OffImm; 0
2303 } else { ----
2304 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = ARM_AM::add; 0
2305 if (OffImm < 0) { 0
2306 AddSub = ARM_AM::sub; 0
2307 OffImm = - OffImm; 0
2308 } ----
2309 int Limit = (1 << 8) * Scale; 0
2310 if (OffImm >= Limit || (OffImm & (Scale-1))) 0
2311 return false; 0
2312 Offset = ARM_AM::getAM3Opc(AddSub, OffImm); 0
2313 } ----
2314 FirstReg = Op0->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2315 SecondReg = Op1->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2316 if (FirstReg == SecondReg) 0
2317 return false; 0
2318 BaseReg = Op0->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
2319 Pred = getInstrPredicate(*Op0, PredReg); 0
2320 dl = Op0->getDebugLoc(); 0
2321 return true; 0
2322 } ----
2323 ----
2324 bool ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt::RescheduleOps( 0
2325 MachineBasicBlock *MBB, SmallVectorImpl &Ops, unsigned Base, ----
2326 bool isLd, DenseMap &MI2LocMap, ----
2327 SmallDenseMap, 8> &RegisterMap) { ----
2328 bool RetVal = false; 0
2329 ----
2330 // Sort by offset (in reverse order). ----
2331 llvm::sort(Ops, [](const MachineInstr *LHS, const MachineInstr *RHS) { 0
2332 int LOffset = getMemoryOpOffset(*LHS); 0
2333 int ROffset = getMemoryOpOffset(*RHS); 0
2334 assert(LHS == RHS || LOffset != ROffset); 0
2335 return LOffset > ROffset; 0
2336 }); ----
2337 ----
2338 // The loads / stores of the same base are in order. Scan them from first to ----
2339 // last and check for the following: ----
2340 // 1. Any def of base. ----
2341 // 2. Any gaps. ----
2342 while (Ops.size() > 1) { 0
2343 unsigned FirstLoc = ~0U; 0
2344 unsigned LastLoc = 0; 0
2345 MachineInstr *FirstOp = nullptr; 0
2346 MachineInstr *LastOp = nullptr; 0
2347 int LastOffset = 0; 0
2348 unsigned LastOpcode = 0; 0
2349 unsigned LastBytes = 0; 0
2350 unsigned NumMove = 0; 0
2351 for (MachineInstr *Op : llvm::reverse(Ops)) { 0
2352 // Make sure each operation has the same kind. ----
2353 unsigned LSMOpcode ----
2354 = getLoadStoreMultipleOpcode(Op->getOpcode(), ARM_AM::ia); 0
2355 if (LastOpcode && LSMOpcode != LastOpcode) 0
2356 break; 0
2357 ----
2358 // Check that we have a continuous set of offsets. ----
2359 int Offset = getMemoryOpOffset(*Op); 0
2360 unsigned Bytes = getLSMultipleTransferSize(Op); 0
2361 if (LastBytes) { 0
2362 if (Bytes != LastBytes || Offset != (LastOffset + (int)Bytes)) 0
2363 break; ----
2364 } ----
2365 ----
2366 // Don't try to reschedule too many instructions. ----
2367 if (NumMove == InstReorderLimit) 0
2368 break; 0
2369 ----
2370 // Found a mergable instruction; save information about it. ----
2371 ++NumMove; 0
2372 LastOffset = Offset; 0
2373 LastBytes = Bytes; 0
2374 LastOpcode = LSMOpcode; 0
2375 ----
2376 unsigned Loc = MI2LocMap[Op]; 0
2377 if (Loc <= FirstLoc) { 0
2378 FirstLoc = Loc; 0
2379 FirstOp = Op; 0
2380 } ----
2381 if (Loc >= LastLoc) { 0
2382 LastLoc = Loc; 0
2383 LastOp = Op; 0
2384 } ----
2385 } ----
2386 ----
2387 if (NumMove <= 1) 0
2388 Ops.pop_back(); 0
2389 else { ----
2390 SmallPtrSet MemOps; 0
2391 SmallSet MemRegs; 0
2392 for (size_t i = Ops.size() - NumMove, e = Ops.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2393 MemOps.insert(Ops[i]); 0
2394 MemRegs.insert(Ops[i]->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
2395 } ----
2396 ----
2397 // Be conservative, if the instructions are too far apart, don't ----
2398 // move them. We want to limit the increase of register pressure. ----
2399 bool DoMove = (LastLoc - FirstLoc) <= NumMove*4; // FIXME: Tune this. 0
2400 if (DoMove) 0
2401 DoMove = IsSafeAndProfitableToMove(isLd, Base, FirstOp, LastOp, 0
2402 MemOps, MemRegs, TRI, AA); ----
2403 if (!DoMove) { 0
2404 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumMove; ++i) 0
2405 Ops.pop_back(); 0
2406 } else { ----
2407 // This is the new location for the loads / stores. ----
2408 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos = isLd ? FirstOp : LastOp; 0
2409 while (InsertPos != MBB->end() && 0
2410 (MemOps.count(&*InsertPos) || InsertPos->isDebugInstr())) 0
2411 ++InsertPos; 0
2412 ----
2413 // If we are moving a pair of loads / stores, see if it makes sense ----
2414 // to try to allocate a pair of registers that can form register pairs. ----
2415 MachineInstr *Op0 = Ops.back(); 0
2416 MachineInstr *Op1 = Ops[Ops.size()-2]; 0
2417 Register FirstReg, SecondReg; 0
2418 Register BaseReg, PredReg; 0
2419 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = ARMCC::AL; 0
2420 bool isT2 = false; 0
2421 unsigned NewOpc = 0; 0
2422 int Offset = 0; 0
2423 DebugLoc dl; 0
2424 if (NumMove == 2 && CanFormLdStDWord(Op0, Op1, dl, NewOpc, 0
2425 FirstReg, SecondReg, BaseReg, ----
2426 Offset, PredReg, Pred, isT2)) { ----
2427 Ops.pop_back(); 0
2428 Ops.pop_back(); 0
2429 ----
2430 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(NewOpc); 0
2431 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = TII->getRegClass(MCID, 0, TRI, *MF); 0
2432 MRI->constrainRegClass(FirstReg, TRC); 0
2433 MRI->constrainRegClass(SecondReg, TRC); 0
2434 ----
2435 // Form the pair instruction. ----
2436 if (isLd) { 0
2437 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPos, dl, MCID) 0
2438 .addReg(FirstReg, RegState::Define) 0
2439 .addReg(SecondReg, RegState::Define) 0
2440 .addReg(BaseReg); 0
2441 // FIXME: We're converting from LDRi12 to an insn that still ----
2442 // uses addrmode2, so we need an explicit offset reg. It should ----
2443 // always by reg0 since we're transforming LDRi12s. ----
2444 if (!isT2) 0
2445 MIB.addReg(0); 0
2446 MIB.addImm(Offset).addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
2447 MIB.cloneMergedMemRefs({Op0, Op1}); 0
2448 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Formed " << *MIB << "\n"); 0
2449 ++NumLDRDFormed; 0
2450 } else { ----
2451 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPos, dl, MCID) 0
2452 .addReg(FirstReg) 0
2453 .addReg(SecondReg) 0
2454 .addReg(BaseReg); 0
2455 // FIXME: We're converting from LDRi12 to an insn that still ----
2456 // uses addrmode2, so we need an explicit offset reg. It should ----
2457 // always by reg0 since we're transforming STRi12s. ----
2458 if (!isT2) 0
2459 MIB.addReg(0); 0
2460 MIB.addImm(Offset).addImm(Pred).addReg(PredReg); 0
2461 MIB.cloneMergedMemRefs({Op0, Op1}); 0
2462 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Formed " << *MIB << "\n"); 0
2463 ++NumSTRDFormed; 0
2464 } ----
2465 MBB->erase(Op0); 0
2466 MBB->erase(Op1); 0
2467 ----
2468 if (!isT2) { 0
2469 // Add register allocation hints to form register pairs. ----
2470 MRI->setRegAllocationHint(FirstReg, ARMRI::RegPairEven, SecondReg); 0
2471 MRI->setRegAllocationHint(SecondReg, ARMRI::RegPairOdd, FirstReg); 0
2472 } ----
2473 } else { ----
2474 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumMove; ++i) { 0
2475 MachineInstr *Op = Ops.pop_back_val(); 0
2476 if (isLd) { 0
2477 // Populate RegisterMap with all Registers defined by loads. ----
2478 Register Reg = Op->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2479 RegisterMap[Reg]; 0
2480 } ----
2481 ----
2482 MBB->splice(InsertPos, MBB, Op); 0
2483 } ----
2484 } ----
2485 ----
2486 NumLdStMoved += NumMove; 0
2487 RetVal = true; 0
2488 } 0
2489 } 0
2490 } ----
2491 ----
2492 return RetVal; 0
2493 } ----
2494 ----
2495 static void forEachDbgRegOperand(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2496 std::function Fn) { ----
2497 if (MI->isNonListDebugValue()) { 0
2498 auto &Op = MI->getOperand(0); 0
2499 if (Op.isReg()) 0
2500 Fn(Op); 0
2501 } else { ----
2502 for (unsigned I = 2; I < MI->getNumOperands(); I++) { 0
2503 auto &Op = MI->getOperand(I); 0
2504 if (Op.isReg()) 0
2505 Fn(Op); 0
2506 } ----
2507 } ----
2508 } 0
2509 ----
2510 // Update the RegisterMap with the instruction that was moved because a ----
2511 // DBG_VALUE_LIST may need to be moved again. ----
2512 static void updateRegisterMapForDbgValueListAfterMove( 0
2513 SmallDenseMap, 8> &RegisterMap, ----
2514 MachineInstr *DbgValueListInstr, MachineInstr *InstrToReplace) { ----
2515 ----
2516 forEachDbgRegOperand(DbgValueListInstr, [&](MachineOperand &Op) { 0
2517 auto RegIt = RegisterMap.find(Op.getReg()); 0
2518 if (RegIt == RegisterMap.end()) 0
2519 return; 0
2520 auto &InstrVec = RegIt->getSecond(); 0
2521 for (unsigned I = 0; I < InstrVec.size(); I++) 0
2522 if (InstrVec[I] == InstrToReplace) 0
2523 InstrVec[I] = DbgValueListInstr; 0
2524 }); ----
2525 } 0
2526 ----
2527 static DebugVariable createDebugVariableFromMachineInstr(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
2528 auto DbgVar = DebugVariable(MI->getDebugVariable(), MI->getDebugExpression(), ----
2529 MI->getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
2530 return DbgVar; 0
2531 } ----
2532 ----
2533 bool ----
2534 ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt::RescheduleLoadStoreInstrs(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
2535 bool RetVal = false; 0
2536 ----
2537 DenseMap MI2LocMap; 0
2538 using MapIt = DenseMap>::iterator; ----
2539 using Base2InstMap = DenseMap>; ----
2540 using BaseVec = SmallVector; ----
2541 Base2InstMap Base2LdsMap; 0
2542 Base2InstMap Base2StsMap; 0
2543 BaseVec LdBases; 0
2544 BaseVec StBases; 0
2545 // This map is used to track the relationship between the virtual ----
2546 // register that is the result of a load that is moved and the DBG_VALUE ----
2547 // MachineInstr pointer that uses that virtual register. ----
2548 SmallDenseMap, 8> RegisterMap; 0
2549 ----
2550 unsigned Loc = 0; 0
2551 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB->begin(); 0
2552 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = MBB->end(); 0
2553 while (MBBI != E) { 0
2554 for (; MBBI != E; ++MBBI) { 0
2555 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2556 if (MI.isCall() || MI.isTerminator()) { 0
2557 // Stop at barriers. ----
2558 ++MBBI; 0
2559 break; 0
2560 } ----
2561 ----
2562 if (!MI.isDebugInstr()) 0
2563 MI2LocMap[&MI] = ++Loc; 0
2564 ----
2565 if (!isMemoryOp(MI)) 0
2566 continue; 0
2567 Register PredReg; 0
2568 if (getInstrPredicate(MI, PredReg) != ARMCC::AL) 0
2569 continue; 0
2570 ----
2571 int Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2572 bool isLd = isLoadSingle(Opc); 0
2573 Register Base = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
2574 int Offset = getMemoryOpOffset(MI); 0
2575 bool StopHere = false; 0
2576 auto FindBases = [&] (Base2InstMap &Base2Ops, BaseVec &Bases) { 0
2577 MapIt BI = Base2Ops.find(Base); 0
2578 if (BI == Base2Ops.end()) { 0
2579 Base2Ops[Base].push_back(&MI); 0
2580 Bases.push_back(Base); 0
2581 return; 0
2582 } ----
2583 for (unsigned i = 0, e = BI->second.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2584 if (Offset == getMemoryOpOffset(*BI->second[i])) { 0
2585 StopHere = true; 0
2586 break; 0
2587 } ----
2588 } ----
2589 if (!StopHere) 0
2590 BI->second.push_back(&MI); 0
2591 }; 0
2592 ----
2593 if (isLd) 0
2594 FindBases(Base2LdsMap, LdBases); 0
2595 else ----
2596 FindBases(Base2StsMap, StBases); 0
2597 ----
2598 if (StopHere) { 0
2599 // Found a duplicate (a base+offset combination that's seen earlier). ----
2600 // Backtrack. ----
2601 --Loc; 0
2602 break; 0
2603 } ----
2604 } ----
2605 ----
2606 // Re-schedule loads. ----
2607 for (unsigned i = 0, e = LdBases.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2608 unsigned Base = LdBases[i]; 0
2609 SmallVectorImpl &Lds = Base2LdsMap[Base]; 0
2610 if (Lds.size() > 1) 0
2611 RetVal |= RescheduleOps(MBB, Lds, Base, true, MI2LocMap, RegisterMap); 0
2612 } ----
2613 ----
2614 // Re-schedule stores. ----
2615 for (unsigned i = 0, e = StBases.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2616 unsigned Base = StBases[i]; 0
2617 SmallVectorImpl &Sts = Base2StsMap[Base]; 0
2618 if (Sts.size() > 1) 0
2619 RetVal |= RescheduleOps(MBB, Sts, Base, false, MI2LocMap, RegisterMap); 0
2620 } ----
2621 ----
2622 if (MBBI != E) { 0
2623 Base2LdsMap.clear(); 0
2624 Base2StsMap.clear(); 0
2625 LdBases.clear(); 0
2626 StBases.clear(); 0
2627 } ----
2628 } ----
2629 ----
2630 // Reschedule DBG_VALUEs to match any loads that were moved. When a load is ----
2631 // sunk beyond a DBG_VALUE that is referring to it, the DBG_VALUE becomes a ----
2632 // use-before-def, resulting in a loss of debug info. ----
2633 ----
2634 // Example: ----
2635 // Before the Pre Register Allocation Load Store Pass ----
2636 // inst_a ----
2637 // %2 = ld ... ----
2638 // inst_b ----
2639 // DBG_VALUE %2, "x", ... ----
2640 // %3 = ld ... ----
2641 ----
2642 // After the Pass: ----
2643 // inst_a ----
2644 // inst_b ----
2645 // DBG_VALUE %2, "x", ... ----
2646 // %2 = ld ... ----
2647 // %3 = ld ... ----
2648 ----
2649 // The code below addresses this by moving the DBG_VALUE to the position ----
2650 // immediately after the load. ----
2651 ----
2652 // Example: ----
2653 // After the code below: ----
2654 // inst_a ----
2655 // inst_b ----
2656 // %2 = ld ... ----
2657 // DBG_VALUE %2, "x", ... ----
2658 // %3 = ld ... ----
2659 ----
2660 // The algorithm works in two phases: First RescheduleOps() populates the ----
2661 // RegisterMap with registers that were moved as keys, there is no value ----
2662 // inserted. In the next phase, every MachineInstr in a basic block is ----
2663 // iterated over. If it is a valid DBG_VALUE or DBG_VALUE_LIST and it uses one ----
2664 // or more registers in the RegisterMap, the RegisterMap and InstrMap are ----
2665 // populated with the MachineInstr. If the DBG_VALUE or DBG_VALUE_LIST ----
2666 // describes debug information for a variable that already exists in the ----
2667 // DbgValueSinkCandidates, the MachineInstr in the DbgValueSinkCandidates must ----
2668 // be set to undef. If the current MachineInstr is a load that was moved, ----
2669 // undef the corresponding DBG_VALUE or DBG_VALUE_LIST and clone it to below ----
2670 // the load. ----
2671 ----
2672 // To illustrate the above algorithm visually let's take this example. ----
2673 ----
2674 // Before the Pre Register Allocation Load Store Pass: ----
2675 // %2 = ld ... ----
2676 // DBG_VALUE %2, A, .... # X ----
2677 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2678 // %3 = ld ... ----
2679 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2680 // %4 = ld ... ----
2681 ----
2682 // After Pre Register Allocation Load Store Pass: ----
2683 // DBG_VALUE %2, A, .... # X ----
2684 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2685 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2686 // %2 = ld ... ----
2687 // %3 = ld ... ----
2688 // %4 = ld ... ----
2689 ----
2690 // The algorithm below does the following: ----
2691 ----
2692 // In the beginning, the RegisterMap will have been populated with the virtual ----
2693 // registers %2, and %3, the DbgValueSinkCandidates and the InstrMap will be ----
2694 // empty. DbgValueSinkCandidates = {}, RegisterMap = {2 -> {}, 3 -> {}}, ----
2695 // InstrMap {} ----
2696 // -> DBG_VALUE %2, A, .... # X ----
2697 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2698 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2699 // %2 = ld ... ----
2700 // %3 = ld ... ----
2701 // %4 = ld ... ----
2702 ----
2703 // After the first DBG_VALUE (denoted with an X) is processed, the ----
2704 // DbgValueSinkCandidates and InstrMap will be populated and the RegisterMap ----
2705 // entry for %2 will be populated as well. DbgValueSinkCandidates = {A -> X}, ----
2706 // RegisterMap = {2 -> {X}, 3 -> {}}, InstrMap {X -> 2} ----
2707 // DBG_VALUE %2, A, .... # X ----
2708 // -> DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2709 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2710 // %2 = ld ... ----
2711 // %3 = ld ... ----
2712 // %4 = ld ... ----
2713 ----
2714 // After the DBG_VALUE Y is processed, the DbgValueSinkCandidates is updated ----
2715 // to now hold Y for A and the RegisterMap is also updated to remove X from ----
2716 // %2, this is because both X and Y describe the same debug variable A. X is ----
2717 // also updated to have a $noreg as the first operand. ----
2718 // DbgValueSinkCandidates = {A -> {Y}}, RegisterMap = {2 -> {}, 3 -> {}}, ----
2719 // InstrMap = {X-> 2} ----
2720 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, .... # X ----
2721 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2722 // -> DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2723 // %2 = ld ... ----
2724 // %3 = ld ... ----
2725 // %4 = ld ... ----
2726 ----
2727 // After DBG_VALUE Z is processed, the DbgValueSinkCandidates is updated to ----
2728 // hold Z fr A, the RegisterMap is updated to hold Z for %3, and the InstrMap ----
2729 // is updated to have Z mapped to %3. This is again because Z describes the ----
2730 // debug variable A, Y is not updated to have $noreg as first operand because ----
2731 // its first operand is an immediate, not a register. ----
2732 // DbgValueSinkCandidates = {A -> {Z}}, RegisterMap = {2 -> {}, 3 -> {Z}}, ----
2733 // InstrMap = {X -> 2, Z -> 3} ----
2734 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, .... # X ----
2735 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2736 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2737 // -> %2 = ld ... ----
2738 // %3 = ld ... ----
2739 // %4 = ld ... ----
2740 ----
2741 // Nothing happens here since the RegisterMap for %2 contains no value. ----
2742 // DbgValueSinkCandidates = {A -> {Z}}, RegisterMap = {2 -> {}, 3 -> {Z}}, ----
2743 // InstrMap = {X -> 2, Z -> 3} ----
2744 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, .... # X ----
2745 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2746 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2747 // %2 = ld ... ----
2748 // -> %3 = ld ... ----
2749 // %4 = ld ... ----
2750 ----
2751 // Since the RegisterMap contains Z as a value for %3, the MachineInstr ----
2752 // pointer Z is copied to come after the load for %3 and the old Z's first ----
2753 // operand is changed to $noreg the Basic Block iterator is moved to after the ----
2754 // DBG_VALUE Z's new position. ----
2755 // DbgValueSinkCandidates = {A -> {Z}}, RegisterMap = {2 -> {}, 3 -> {Z}}, ----
2756 // InstrMap = {X -> 2, Z -> 3} ----
2757 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, .... # X ----
2758 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2759 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, ..., # Old Z ----
2760 // %2 = ld ... ----
2761 // %3 = ld ... ----
2762 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2763 // -> %4 = ld ... ----
2764 ----
2765 // Nothing happens for %4 and the algorithm exits having processed the entire ----
2766 // Basic Block. ----
2767 // DbgValueSinkCandidates = {A -> {Z}}, RegisterMap = {2 -> {}, 3 -> {Z}}, ----
2768 // InstrMap = {X -> 2, Z -> 3} ----
2769 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, .... # X ----
2770 // DBG_VALUE 0, A, ... # Y ----
2771 // DBG_VALUE $noreg, A, ..., # Old Z ----
2772 // %2 = ld ... ----
2773 // %3 = ld ... ----
2774 // DBG_VALUE %3, A, ..., # Z ----
2775 // %4 = ld ... ----
2776 ----
2777 // This map is used to track the relationship between ----
2778 // a Debug Variable and the DBG_VALUE MachineInstr pointer that describes the ----
2779 // debug information for that Debug Variable. ----
2780 SmallDenseMap DbgValueSinkCandidates; 0
2781 // This map is used to track the relationship between a DBG_VALUE or ----
2782 // DBG_VALUE_LIST MachineInstr pointer and Registers that it uses. ----
2783 SmallDenseMap, 8> InstrMap; 0
2784 for (MBBI = MBB->begin(), E = MBB->end(); MBBI != E; ++MBBI) { 0
2785 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2786 ----
2787 auto PopulateRegisterAndInstrMapForDebugInstr = [&](Register Reg) { 0
2788 auto RegIt = RegisterMap.find(Reg); 0
2789 if (RegIt == RegisterMap.end()) 0
2790 return; 0
2791 auto &InstrVec = RegIt->getSecond(); 0
2792 InstrVec.push_back(&MI); 0
2793 InstrMap[&MI].push_back(Reg); 0
2794 }; 0
2795 ----
2796 if (MI.isDebugValue()) { 0
2797 assert(MI.getDebugVariable() && 0
2798 "DBG_VALUE or DBG_VALUE_LIST must contain a DILocalVariable"); ----
2799 ----
2800 auto DbgVar = createDebugVariableFromMachineInstr(&MI); 0
2801 // If the first operand is a register and it exists in the RegisterMap, we ----
2802 // know this is a DBG_VALUE that uses the result of a load that was moved, ----
2803 // and is therefore a candidate to also be moved, add it to the ----
2804 // RegisterMap and InstrMap. ----
2805 forEachDbgRegOperand(&MI, [&](MachineOperand &Op) { 0
2806 PopulateRegisterAndInstrMapForDebugInstr(Op.getReg()); 0
2807 }); 0
2808 ----
2809 // If the current DBG_VALUE describes the same variable as one of the ----
2810 // in-flight DBG_VALUEs, remove the candidate from the list and set it to ----
2811 // undef. Moving one DBG_VALUE past another would result in the variable's ----
2812 // value going back in time when stepping through the block in the ----
2813 // debugger. ----
2814 auto InstrIt = DbgValueSinkCandidates.find(DbgVar); 0
2815 if (InstrIt != DbgValueSinkCandidates.end()) { 0
2816 auto *Instr = InstrIt->getSecond(); 0
2817 auto RegIt = InstrMap.find(Instr); 0
2818 if (RegIt != InstrMap.end()) { 0
2819 const auto &RegVec = RegIt->getSecond(); 0
2820 // For every Register in the RegVec, remove the MachineInstr in the ----
2821 // RegisterMap that describes the DbgVar. ----
2822 for (auto &Reg : RegVec) { 0
2823 auto RegIt = RegisterMap.find(Reg); 0
2824 if (RegIt == RegisterMap.end()) 0
2825 continue; 0
2826 auto &InstrVec = RegIt->getSecond(); 0
2827 auto IsDbgVar = [&](MachineInstr *I) -> bool { 0
2828 auto Var = createDebugVariableFromMachineInstr(I); 0
2829 return Var == DbgVar; 0
2830 }; 0
2831 ----
2832 InstrVec.erase( 0
2833 std::remove_if(InstrVec.begin(), InstrVec.end(), IsDbgVar), 0
2834 InstrVec.end()); 0
2835 } ----
2836 forEachDbgRegOperand(Instr, 0
2837 [&](MachineOperand &Op) { Op.setReg(0); }); 0
2838 } ----
2839 } ----
2840 DbgValueSinkCandidates[DbgVar] = &MI; 0
2841 } else { ----
2842 // If the first operand of a load matches with a DBG_VALUE in RegisterMap, ----
2843 // then move that DBG_VALUE to below the load. ----
2844 auto Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2845 if (!isLoadSingle(Opc)) 0
2846 continue; 0
2847 auto Reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2848 auto RegIt = RegisterMap.find(Reg); 0
2849 if (RegIt == RegisterMap.end()) 0
2850 continue; 0
2851 auto &DbgInstrVec = RegIt->getSecond(); 0
2852 if (!DbgInstrVec.size()) 0
2853 continue; 0
2854 for (auto *DbgInstr : DbgInstrVec) { 0
2855 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos = std::next(MBBI); 0
2856 auto *ClonedMI = MI.getMF()->CloneMachineInstr(DbgInstr); 0
2857 MBB->insert(InsertPos, ClonedMI); 0
2858 MBBI++; 0
2859 // Erase the entry into the DbgValueSinkCandidates for the DBG_VALUE ----
2860 // that was moved. ----
2861 auto DbgVar = createDebugVariableFromMachineInstr(DbgInstr); 0
2862 auto DbgIt = DbgValueSinkCandidates.find(DbgVar); 0
2863 // If the instruction is a DBG_VALUE_LIST, it may have already been ----
2864 // erased from the DbgValueSinkCandidates. Only erase if it exists in ----
2865 // the DbgValueSinkCandidates. ----
2866 if (DbgIt != DbgValueSinkCandidates.end()) 0
2867 DbgValueSinkCandidates.erase(DbgIt); 0
2868 // Zero out original dbg instr ----
2869 forEachDbgRegOperand(DbgInstr, 0
2870 [&](MachineOperand &Op) { Op.setReg(0); }); 0
2871 // Update RegisterMap with ClonedMI because it might have to be moved ----
2872 // again. ----
2873 if (DbgInstr->isDebugValueList()) 0
2874 updateRegisterMapForDbgValueListAfterMove(RegisterMap, ClonedMI, 0
2875 DbgInstr); ----
2876 } ----
2877 } ----
2878 } ----
2879 return RetVal; 0
2880 } 0
2881 ----
2882 // Get the Base register operand index from the memory access MachineInst if we ----
2883 // should attempt to distribute postinc on it. Return -1 if not of a valid ----
2884 // instruction type. If it returns an index, it is assumed that instruction is a ----
2885 // r+i indexing mode, and getBaseOperandIndex() + 1 is the Offset index. ----
2886 static int getBaseOperandIndex(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2887 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
2888 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16: 0
2889 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32: ----
2890 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16: ----
2891 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32: ----
2892 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32: ----
2893 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32: ----
2894 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8: ----
2895 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16: ----
2896 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32: ----
2897 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB16: ----
2898 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB32: ----
2899 case ARM::MVE_VSTRH32: ----
2900 case ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8: ----
2901 case ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16: ----
2902 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32: ----
2903 case ARM::t2LDRHi8: ----
2904 case ARM::t2LDRHi12: ----
2905 case ARM::t2LDRSHi8: ----
2906 case ARM::t2LDRSHi12: ----
2907 case ARM::t2LDRBi8: ----
2908 case ARM::t2LDRBi12: ----
2909 case ARM::t2LDRSBi8: ----
2910 case ARM::t2LDRSBi12: ----
2911 case ARM::t2STRBi8: ----
2912 case ARM::t2STRBi12: ----
2913 case ARM::t2STRHi8: ----
2914 case ARM::t2STRHi12: ----
2915 return 1; 0
2916 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16_post: 0
2917 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32_post: ----
2918 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16_post: ----
2919 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32_post: ----
2920 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32_post: ----
2921 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32_post: ----
2922 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8_post: ----
2923 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16_post: ----
2924 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32_post: ----
2925 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB16_post: ----
2926 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB32_post: ----
2927 case ARM::MVE_VSTRH32_post: ----
2928 case ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8_post: ----
2929 case ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16_post: ----
2930 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32_post: ----
2931 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16_pre: ----
2932 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32_pre: ----
2933 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16_pre: ----
2934 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32_pre: ----
2935 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32_pre: ----
2936 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32_pre: ----
2937 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8_pre: ----
2938 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16_pre: ----
2939 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32_pre: ----
2940 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB16_pre: ----
2941 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB32_pre: ----
2942 case ARM::MVE_VSTRH32_pre: ----
2943 case ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8_pre: ----
2944 case ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16_pre: ----
2945 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32_pre: ----
2946 return 2; 0
2947 } ----
2948 return -1; 0
2949 } ----
2950 ----
2951 static bool isPostIndex(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2952 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
2953 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16_post: 0
2954 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32_post: ----
2955 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16_post: ----
2956 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32_post: ----
2957 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32_post: ----
2958 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32_post: ----
2959 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8_post: ----
2960 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16_post: ----
2961 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32_post: ----
2962 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB16_post: ----
2963 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB32_post: ----
2964 case ARM::MVE_VSTRH32_post: ----
2965 case ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8_post: ----
2966 case ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16_post: ----
2967 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32_post: ----
2968 return true; 0
2969 } ----
2970 return false; 0
2971 } ----
2972 ----
2973 static bool isPreIndex(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2974 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
2975 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS16_pre: 0
2976 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBS32_pre: ----
2977 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU16_pre: ----
2978 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU32_pre: ----
2979 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHS32_pre: ----
2980 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU32_pre: ----
2981 case ARM::MVE_VLDRBU8_pre: ----
2982 case ARM::MVE_VLDRHU16_pre: ----
2983 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32_pre: ----
2984 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB16_pre: ----
2985 case ARM::MVE_VSTRB32_pre: ----
2986 case ARM::MVE_VSTRH32_pre: ----
2987 case ARM::MVE_VSTRBU8_pre: ----
2988 case ARM::MVE_VSTRHU16_pre: ----
2989 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32_pre: ----
2990 return true; 0
2991 } ----
2992 return false; 0
2993 } ----
2994 ----
2995 // Given a memory access Opcode, check that the give Imm would be a valid Offset ----
2996 // for this instruction (same as isLegalAddressImm), Or if the instruction ----
2997 // could be easily converted to one where that was valid. For example converting ----
2998 // t2LDRi12 to t2LDRi8 for negative offsets. Works in conjunction with ----
2999 // AdjustBaseAndOffset below. ----
3000 static bool isLegalOrConvertableAddressImm(unsigned Opcode, int Imm, 0
3001 const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
3002 int &CodesizeEstimate) { ----
3003 if (isLegalAddressImm(Opcode, Imm, TII)) 0
3004 return true; 0
3005 ----
3006 // We can convert AddrModeT2_i12 to AddrModeT2_i8neg. ----
3007 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = TII->get(Opcode); 0
3008 unsigned AddrMode = (Desc.TSFlags & ARMII::AddrModeMask); 0
3009 switch (AddrMode) { 0
3010 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i12: 0
3011 CodesizeEstimate += 1; 0
3012 return Imm < 0 && -Imm < ((1 << 8) * 1); 0
3013 } ----
3014 return false; 0
3015 } ----
3016 ----
3017 // Given an MI adjust its address BaseReg to use NewBaseReg and address offset ----
3018 // by -Offset. This can either happen in-place or be a replacement as MI is ----
3019 // converted to another instruction type. ----
3020 static void AdjustBaseAndOffset(MachineInstr *MI, Register NewBaseReg, 0
3021 int Offset, const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
3022 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
3023 // Set the Base reg ----
3024 unsigned BaseOp = getBaseOperandIndex(*MI); 0
3025 MI->getOperand(BaseOp).setReg(NewBaseReg); 0
3026 // and constrain the reg class to that required by the instruction. ----
3027 MachineFunction *MF = MI->getMF(); 0
3028 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
3029 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(MI->getOpcode()); 0
3030 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = TII->getRegClass(MCID, BaseOp, TRI, *MF); 0
3031 MRI.constrainRegClass(NewBaseReg, TRC); 0
3032 ----
3033 int OldOffset = MI->getOperand(BaseOp + 1).getImm(); 0
3034 if (isLegalAddressImm(MI->getOpcode(), OldOffset - Offset, TII)) 0
3035 MI->getOperand(BaseOp + 1).setImm(OldOffset - Offset); 0
3036 else { ----
3037 unsigned ConvOpcode; ----
3038 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
3039 case ARM::t2LDRHi12: 0
3040 ConvOpcode = ARM::t2LDRHi8; 0
3041 break; 0
3042 case ARM::t2LDRSHi12: 0
3043 ConvOpcode = ARM::t2LDRSHi8; 0
3044 break; 0
3045 case ARM::t2LDRBi12: 0
3046 ConvOpcode = ARM::t2LDRBi8; 0
3047 break; 0
3048 case ARM::t2LDRSBi12: 0
3049 ConvOpcode = ARM::t2LDRSBi8; 0
3050 break; 0
3051 case ARM::t2STRHi12: 0
3052 ConvOpcode = ARM::t2STRHi8; 0
3053 break; 0
3054 case ARM::t2STRBi12: 0
3055 ConvOpcode = ARM::t2STRBi8; 0
3056 break; 0
3057 default: 0
3058 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled convertable opcode"); 0
3059 } ----
3060 assert(isLegalAddressImm(ConvOpcode, OldOffset - Offset, TII) && 0
3061 "Illegal Address Immediate after convert!"); ----
3062 ----
3063 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(ConvOpcode); 0
3064 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), MCID) 0
3065 .add(MI->getOperand(0)) 0
3066 .add(MI->getOperand(1)) 0
3067 .addImm(OldOffset - Offset) 0
3068 .add(MI->getOperand(3)) 0
3069 .add(MI->getOperand(4)) 0
3070 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
3071 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
3072 } ----
3073 } 0
3074 ----
3075 static MachineInstr *createPostIncLoadStore(MachineInstr *MI, int Offset, 0
3076 Register NewReg, ----
3077 const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
3078 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
3079 MachineFunction *MF = MI->getMF(); 0
3080 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
3081 ----
3082 unsigned NewOpcode = getPostIndexedLoadStoreOpcode( 0
3083 MI->getOpcode(), Offset > 0 ? ARM_AM::add : ARM_AM::sub); ----
3084 ----
3085 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(NewOpcode); 0
3086 // Constrain the def register class ----
3087 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = TII->getRegClass(MCID, 0, TRI, *MF); 0
3088 MRI.constrainRegClass(NewReg, TRC); 0
3089 // And do the same for the base operand ----
3090 TRC = TII->getRegClass(MCID, 2, TRI, *MF); 0
3091 MRI.constrainRegClass(MI->getOperand(1).getReg(), TRC); 0
3092 ----
3093 unsigned AddrMode = (MCID.TSFlags & ARMII::AddrModeMask); 0
3094 switch (AddrMode) { 0
3095 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i7: 0
3096 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i7s2: ----
3097 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i7s4: ----
3098 // Any MVE load/store ----
3099 return BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), MCID) 0
3100 .addReg(NewReg, RegState::Define) 0
3101 .add(MI->getOperand(0)) 0
3102 .add(MI->getOperand(1)) 0
3103 .addImm(Offset) 0
3104 .add(MI->getOperand(3)) 0
3105 .add(MI->getOperand(4)) 0
3106 .add(MI->getOperand(5)) 0
3107 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
3108 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i8: 0
3109 if (MI->mayLoad()) { 0
3110 return BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), MCID) 0
3111 .add(MI->getOperand(0)) 0
3112 .addReg(NewReg, RegState::Define) 0
3113 .add(MI->getOperand(1)) 0
3114 .addImm(Offset) 0
3115 .add(MI->getOperand(3)) 0
3116 .add(MI->getOperand(4)) 0
3117 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
3118 } else { ----
3119 return BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), MCID) 0
3120 .addReg(NewReg, RegState::Define) 0
3121 .add(MI->getOperand(0)) 0
3122 .add(MI->getOperand(1)) 0
3123 .addImm(Offset) 0
3124 .add(MI->getOperand(3)) 0
3125 .add(MI->getOperand(4)) 0
3126 .cloneMemRefs(*MI); 0
3127 } ----
3128 default: 0
3129 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled createPostIncLoadStore"); 0
3130 } ----
3131 } ----
3132 ----
3133 // Given a Base Register, optimise the load/store uses to attempt to create more ----
3134 // post-inc accesses and less register moves. We do this by taking zero offset ----
3135 // loads/stores with an add, and convert them to a postinc load/store of the ----
3136 // same type. Any subsequent accesses will be adjusted to use and account for ----
3137 // the post-inc value. ----
3138 // For example: ----
3139 // LDR #0 LDR_POSTINC #16 ----
3140 // LDR #4 LDR #-12 ----
3141 // LDR #8 LDR #-8 ----
3142 // LDR #12 LDR #-4 ----
3143 // ADD #16 ----
3144 // ----
3145 // At the same time if we do not find an increment but do find an existing ----
3146 // pre/post inc instruction, we can still adjust the offsets of subsequent ----
3147 // instructions to save the register move that would otherwise be needed for the ----
3148 // in-place increment. ----
3149 bool ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt::DistributeIncrements(Register Base) { 0
3150 // We are looking for: ----
3151 // One zero offset load/store that can become postinc ----
3152 MachineInstr *BaseAccess = nullptr; 0
3153 MachineInstr *PrePostInc = nullptr; 0
3154 // An increment that can be folded in ----
3155 MachineInstr *Increment = nullptr; 0
3156 // Other accesses after BaseAccess that will need to be updated to use the ----
3157 // postinc value. ----
3158 SmallPtrSet OtherAccesses; 0
3159 for (auto &Use : MRI->use_nodbg_instructions(Base)) { 0
3160 if (!Increment && getAddSubImmediate(Use) != 0) { 0
3161 Increment = &Use; 0
3162 continue; 0
3163 } ----
3164 ----
3165 int BaseOp = getBaseOperandIndex(Use); 0
3166 if (BaseOp == -1) 0
3167 return false; 0
3168 ----
3169 if (!Use.getOperand(BaseOp).isReg() || 0
3170 Use.getOperand(BaseOp).getReg() != Base) 0
3171 return false; 0
3172 if (isPreIndex(Use) || isPostIndex(Use)) 0
3173 PrePostInc = &Use; 0
3174 else if (Use.getOperand(BaseOp + 1).getImm() == 0) 0
3175 BaseAccess = &Use; 0
3176 else ----
3177 OtherAccesses.insert(&Use); 0
3178 } ----
3179 ----
3180 int IncrementOffset; ----
3181 Register NewBaseReg; 0
3182 if (BaseAccess && Increment) { 0
3183 if (PrePostInc || BaseAccess->getParent() != Increment->getParent()) 0
3184 return false; 0
3185 Register PredReg; 0
3186 if (Increment->definesRegister(ARM::CPSR) || 0
3187 getInstrPredicate(*Increment, PredReg) != ARMCC::AL) 0
3188 return false; 0
3189 ----
3190 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nAttempting to distribute increments on VirtualReg " 0
3191 << Base.virtRegIndex() << "\n"); ----
3192 ----
3193 // Make sure that Increment has no uses before BaseAccess that are not PHI ----
3194 // uses. ----
3195 for (MachineInstr &Use : 0
3196 MRI->use_nodbg_instructions(Increment->getOperand(0).getReg())) { 0
3197 if (&Use == BaseAccess || (Use.getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::PHI && 0
3198 !DT->dominates(BaseAccess, &Use))) { 0
3199 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " BaseAccess doesn't dominate use of increment\n"); 0
3200 return false; 0
3201 } ----
3202 } ----
3203 ----
3204 // Make sure that Increment can be folded into Base ----
3205 IncrementOffset = getAddSubImmediate(*Increment); 0
3206 unsigned NewPostIncOpcode = getPostIndexedLoadStoreOpcode( 0
3207 BaseAccess->getOpcode(), IncrementOffset > 0 ? ARM_AM::add : ARM_AM::sub); ----
3208 if (!isLegalAddressImm(NewPostIncOpcode, IncrementOffset, TII)) { 0
3209 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Illegal addressing mode immediate on postinc\n"); 0
3210 return false; 0
3211 } ----
3212 } 0
3213 else if (PrePostInc) { 0
3214 // If we already have a pre/post index load/store then set BaseAccess, ----
3215 // IncrementOffset and NewBaseReg to the values it already produces, ----
3216 // allowing us to update and subsequent uses of BaseOp reg with the ----
3217 // incremented value. ----
3218 if (Increment) 0
3219 return false; 0
3220 ----
3221 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nAttempting to distribute increments on already " 0
3222 << "indexed VirtualReg " << Base.virtRegIndex() << "\n"); ----
3223 int BaseOp = getBaseOperandIndex(*PrePostInc); 0
3224 IncrementOffset = PrePostInc->getOperand(BaseOp+1).getImm(); 0
3225 BaseAccess = PrePostInc; 0
3226 NewBaseReg = PrePostInc->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3227 } ----
3228 else ----
3229 return false; 0
3230 ----
3231 // And make sure that the negative value of increment can be added to all ----
3232 // other offsets after the BaseAccess. We rely on either ----
3233 // dominates(BaseAccess, OtherAccess) or dominates(OtherAccess, BaseAccess) ----
3234 // to keep things simple. ----
3235 // This also adds a simple codesize metric, to detect if an instruction (like ----
3236 // t2LDRBi12) which can often be shrunk to a thumb1 instruction (tLDRBi) ----
3237 // cannot because it is converted to something else (t2LDRBi8). We start this ----
3238 // at -1 for the gain from removing the increment. ----
3239 SmallPtrSet SuccessorAccesses; 0
3240 int CodesizeEstimate = -1; 0
3241 for (auto *Use : OtherAccesses) { 0
3242 if (DT->dominates(BaseAccess, Use)) { 0
3243 SuccessorAccesses.insert(Use); 0
3244 unsigned BaseOp = getBaseOperandIndex(*Use); 0
3245 if (!isLegalOrConvertableAddressImm(Use->getOpcode(), 0
3246 Use->getOperand(BaseOp + 1).getImm() - 0
3247 IncrementOffset, ----
3248 TII, CodesizeEstimate)) { ----
3249 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Illegal addressing mode immediate on use\n"); 0
3250 return false; 0
3251 } ----
3252 } else if (!DT->dominates(Use, BaseAccess)) { 0
3253 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
3254 dbgs() << " Unknown dominance relation between Base and Use\n"); ----
3255 return false; 0
3256 } ----
3257 } ----
3258 if (STI->hasMinSize() && CodesizeEstimate > 0) { 0
3259 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Expected to grow instructions under minsize\n"); 0
3260 return false; 0
3261 } ----
3262 ----
3263 if (!PrePostInc) { 0
3264 // Replace BaseAccess with a post inc ----
3265 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Changing: "; BaseAccess->dump()); 0
3266 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " And : "; Increment->dump()); 0
3267 NewBaseReg = Increment->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3268 MachineInstr *BaseAccessPost = ----
3269 createPostIncLoadStore(BaseAccess, IncrementOffset, NewBaseReg, TII, TRI); 0
3270 BaseAccess->eraseFromParent(); 0
3271 Increment->eraseFromParent(); 0
3272 (void)BaseAccessPost; ----
3273 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " To : "; BaseAccessPost->dump()); 0
3274 } ----
3275 ----
3276 for (auto *Use : SuccessorAccesses) { 0
3277 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Changing: "; Use->dump()); 0
3278 AdjustBaseAndOffset(Use, NewBaseReg, IncrementOffset, TII, TRI); 0
3279 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " To : "; Use->dump()); 0
3280 } ----
3281 ----
3282 // Remove the kill flag from all uses of NewBaseReg, in case any old uses ----
3283 // remain. ----
3284 for (MachineOperand &Op : MRI->use_nodbg_operands(NewBaseReg)) 0
3285 Op.setIsKill(false); 0
3286 return true; 0
3287 } 0
3288 ----
3289 bool ARMPreAllocLoadStoreOpt::DistributeIncrements() { 0
3290 bool Changed = false; 0
3291 SmallSetVector Visited; 0
3292 for (auto &MBB : *MF) { 0
3293 for (auto &MI : MBB) { 0
3294 int BaseOp = getBaseOperandIndex(MI); 0
3295 if (BaseOp == -1 || !MI.getOperand(BaseOp).isReg()) 0
3296 continue; 0
3297 ----
3298 Register Base = MI.getOperand(BaseOp).getReg(); 0
